title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Form into individual balls.
Place balls on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Freeze.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan, stir in water. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened and clear.
Remove from heat, stir in gelatin.
Cool.
Place strawberries in cooled shell.
Pour glaze over berries. Refrigerate pie before serving.
Top with whipped cream.

title: italian style seafood stew
directions: Combine garlic, onion, tomatoes and seasonings in saucepan. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cod or whitefish and simmer gently 2 minutes.
Add scallops and simmer 2 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer 3 to 5 minutes just until shrimp turn pink.
Yields 3 servings. Each serving equals 3 1/2 ounces protein and 1 cup cooked vegetable portion.

title: liver pate
directions: Cream braunschweiger and cream cheese at room temperature. Mix curry powder and soup mix. Refrigerate for several hours. Mold into a ball and roll in parsley flakes or crushed nuts if desired.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Wash and cap berries.
Cover with boiling water and let stand for 3 minutes.
Drain well.
Pour 4 cups of sugar over berries and bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool. When cool, add remaining sugar and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 more minutes and remove from heat.
Let stand overnight.
Place in sterilized jars next morning.
Sealing is not necessary.
Do not double recipe.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour and baking soda; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in semi-sweet morsels and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen 2 1/4 inch cookies.

title: stuffed french toast breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread and cube.
Place 1/2 of bread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cube cream cheese and place on top of bread layer. Top with remaining bread.
Mix eggs, syrup and milk.
Pour over layers.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: corn dog and onion ring batter
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip hot dogs or onion rings in batter; fry in hot oil.

title: debbie's chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add tomato juice and beans.
Add chili powder.
Simmer about 1 hour, then it's ready.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening; add brown and white sugars and cream again. Stir in well beaten egg yolks. Sift flour with baking powder; add alternately with milk. Add nuts and vanilla. Fold in well beaten egg whites. Bake in greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Frost the top with powdered sugar icing, allowing it to drip down the sides. Fix nut halves and bits of candied fruits on top.
Slice thinly to serve.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients first.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: "gude" meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into a loaf.
Spray loaf with Pam. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Bake with ketchup during the last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix peanut butter, shortening, sugars, and water.
Stir in baking mix.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten cookies in crisscross pattern with fork dipped in flour. Bake until set, 5-7 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet.
Make about 4 doz. cookies.

title: herb cheese spread
directions: Spread
mustard over top of cheese; sprinkle with parsley flakes and next four ingredients.
Place cheese, mustard side down, in center of pastry.
Wrap package style, trimming excess pastry.
Seal seam. Place seam side down on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Brush with egg; chill 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes; brush with egg, and bake an additional 10 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm with assorted crackers or sliced apples or pears. Yield: 8 to 10 appetizer servings.

title: holly wreath cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar; cream well.
Add vanilla.
Slowly add sifted flour; mix well.
Put through cookie press.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish (greased) and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: little smokies wrapped in bacon
directions: Grease bottom of glass dish 9 x 13.
Wrap smokies in bacon; cut bacon in 1/2 or 1/3.
(I use the thick slices and cut it in 1/3 slices.)
Use toothpicks to hold bacon.
Lay in pan, pour brown sugar over tops (use the full box).
Cover with foil - let set on counter for 24 hours.
Bake 350 degrees for 45 minutes uncovered until bacon is done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut bread in cubes and place in a 9x13 inch casserole dish. Spread meat (ham, sausage or bacon) and mushrooms over bread. Mix the salt, mustard pepper, eggs and milk together and pour over bread and meat. Grate and top casserole with cheese. Bake 1 hr. at 325 degrees.

title: holiday ribbon ring
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour into a 6-cup ring pan.
Chill until set, but not firm, about 15 minutes in refrigerator.

Chill remaining gelatin in bowl; gradually blend in 1/3 cup sour cream. Spoon over gelatin in mold. Chill until set but not firm, about 15 minutes. Repeat procedure using lime gelatin, remaining 2 1/2 cups boiling water and 1/3 cup sour cream.
Chill 2 hours; unmold.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cornbread cake (olivia's)
directions: Combine in

large bowl the canola oil and sugar until slightly dissolved. Add to mixture the eggs and vanilla and mix. Next add flour and thoroughly blend. Blend in nuts and pour into greased 9 x 13 baking pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pina colada cake no. 1
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions and bake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
(Note: No mention is made of greasing pan, but I would advise doing so.)
While cake is baking, blend condensed milk and cream of coconut in bowl.
As soon as cake is removed from oven, invert onto serving dish and puncture with as many holes as possible, using a fork.
Then pour the milk-cream of coconut mixture into the holes.
Refrigerate the cake.
Next day or when cake is cool, mix thawed coconut with Cool Whip and ice the cake with this.
Return cake to refrigerator until ready to serve.
Refrigerate any leftover cake.

title: aunt velma brown's candy
directions: Melt butter and 1 cup sugar in heavy iron skillet.
Pour slowly over remaining sugar and cream.
Cook to firm boil stage (246°), stirring constantly to prevent burning.
Remove from heat. Add soda and stir.
Add butter and cool 10 minutes. Add vanilla and beat until stiff.
Blend in pecans.
Pour in greased pan and cut into squares.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together butter and shortening with sugar.
Add one egg at a time and the milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add to mixture.
Then add vanilla.
Mix and bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
When cool, frost with the icing.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers.
Melt marshmallows in cream.
Mix all ingredients and form into loaf.
Store in refrigerator at least a week before cutting so flavors blend.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Cream the oleo and brown sugar; add flour and nuts.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 2 cups for topping.
Press in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: the wonder cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Mix together last 2 ingredients.
Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Pour 1/2 of cake mixture into pan; add sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Add remaining batter.
Using a knife, twirl sugar mixture throughout batter. Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add soda and vanilla.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for one hour (or a little less, depending on your oven).

title: easy casserole (leftover roast beef)
directions: Mix gravy as directed on package.
Pour into Pyrex dish.
Slice roast and put into gravy mix.
Layer alternately with onion and potatoes.
Cover with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: ritubarb dessert
directions: Put rhubarb, sugar, dry Jell-O and dry cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order listed.
Do not mix; pour hot water over first 4 ingredients; then pour melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Fresh or frozen rhubarb may be used. Cool before cutting and store in refrigerator.

title: white fudge
directions: Heat and beat in double boiler cream cheese, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Heat pecans in 1 tablespoon butter (can heat in microwave); add to other mixture.
Press into pan or drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: stuffed summer squash
directions: Cut squash in halves lengthwise.
Cook for 2 minutes in boiling salted water.
Drain them dry and remove the centers. Place them on a shallow buttered dish; fill with mixture of half sausage-meat and half mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over the top; dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 2 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Add warm water and warmed buttermilk to yeast.
Blend flour, baking powder, soda, sugar and salt.
Add shortening, butter or margarine; add to flour mixture.
Cut into coarse meal, use pastry blender (or 2 knives).
Stir in buttermilk and yeast.
Turn onto floured board and knead lightly.
Roll to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into circles with floured glass or biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda into bowl. Stir in oatmeal.
Add egg, oil, milk, banana and nuts, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar, Karo, whipping cream and milk and beat more.
Then add the salt and vanilla.
Freeze in freezer until firm.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift dry ingredients and mix in by hand.
Stir in chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: sangria
directions: Mix together and chill for 2 hours before serving.
You may add sugar, if desired.

title: sollie's poke salad
directions: Gather tender poke leaves.
Wash thoroughly as for any other leafy green vegetable.
Remove the stems and boil the leaves in a large, heavy pot of salty water.
Boil for approximately 5 minutes, stirring periodically.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix Sauterne and brandy.
Pour over ice, then add champagne and sparkling water.
Serve immediately.
Serves 30.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cream cracker crumbs and 1/4 lb. butter.
Line bottom of 9x5 in baking dish with one half of creamed mixture.
Drain asparagus and arrange over crumbs.
Make white sauce with 4 T. butter, flour, and milk.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour over asparagus and top with remaining crumbs, and slivered almonds. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender in salted water.
Drain and mash through ricer.
Add garlic salt, onion, cheese, cracker crumbs and milk.
Grease dish.
Put ingredients in dish and place 1/2 cup of cracker crumbs on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: foolproof turkey(herb-marinated turkey and gravy)
directions: Stir together water, salt, brown sugar in a large pot until salt and sugar dissolve. Add in 1 bunch fresh thyme, garlic, black peppercorns and a 12 to 15 lb turkey. Refrigerate 12 to 18 hours. Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Drain turkey, discard marinade. Tuck wings under turkey, tie legs together.
Place the carrots, celery, onions and 1 c canned chicken broth in a large roasting pan.
Rub turkey with olive oil, place on top of vegetables in pan and roast for 3 to 3 1/2 hours until thermometer inserted into thickest part of thigh registers 180 degrees.
Cover turkey loosely with foil if
browning too quickly. Discard vegetables, pour pan juices into a large measuring cup and add more chicken broth to make 4 cups.
Melt 4 Tbsp butter in saucepan over medium heat. Add flour and whisk, 2 minutes. Gradually whisk in broth mixture, heavy cream and pepper.
Bring to a boil and cook, whisking constantly, until thickened. Makes 16 servings.

title: cinnamon toast spread
directions: Cream all ingredients thoroughly and store in covered container in refrigerator.
Spread on hot toast, hot French toast or biscuits.

title: mother mac's "kottbullar"(swedish meatballs)
directions: Put crumbs in large bowl.
Cover with hot water.
Let stand a few minutes.
Mix in remaining ingredients, except onion.
Form into balls.
Meanwhile, slice onion into a little oil in skillet; brown.
Remove onion and add meatballs and brown.
Return onion to meatballs in skillet; add water and 3 or 4 whole allspice.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Makes its own natural gravy. Allspice is the secret to the flavor.
(I usually double this recipe.)

title: 7 minute icing
directions: Combine all ingredients but vanilla in top of double boiler. Cook over boiling water, beating constantly, for 7 minutes, until icing stands in stiff peak.
Remove from heat and beat in vanilla.

title: hot baked buns
directions: Grate cheese and add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Take centers out of hard rolls and fill with mixture.
Wrap in foil. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
These can be frozen and baked at 325° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: italian chili
directions: Crumble beef into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Stir in onion, green pepper, celery and garlic.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 to 8 minutes, until beef is done and vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring twice to break apart.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Recover and microwave at High for 20 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Microwave, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes until flavors are well blended.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients except hamburger buns.
Mix well, then spread on buns.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° until cheese is melted and slightly browned.

title: beefy tortilla soup
directions: *I drain off the liquid at the top of the can, but I don't drain and rinse them.

title: hash browns
directions: Thaw packaged hash browns to separate.
Mix soup, sour cream, onion and parsley.
Pour over hash browns.
Garnish with paprika. Bake in 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish covered loosely at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 350°. Casserole made of canned ingredients you have on hand when unexpected company drops by.
Serve with fruit.

title: quick cheesy potato soup
directions: Chop onion, carrots and green pepper in a food processor. In a large pot coated with nonstick cooking spray, saut the chopped vegetables over medium heat until tender, about 5 minutes. Add the soup, chicken broth, and cheese stirring until the cheese is melted and the soup is well heated. Before serving stir in the yogurt; do not boil.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend the cream soups and milk together; mix 1/2 of this with rice and pour into pan.
Place chicken (skin side up) on top of soup/rice mixture.
Pour remaining milk/soup mixture over the chicken.
Sprinkle dried onion soup on top.
Bake uncovered in oven at 350° for 60 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: creamy chicken salad
directions: In a medium-size bowl, combine chicken, zucchini, spinach, carrots and walnuts; toss.

title: million dollar spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Saute beef in butter until brown. Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, scallions and green pepper.

title: chicken mandolay
directions: Mix flour, curry and salt in bag. Shake chicken in bag.
Brown in oil.
Place chicken in oven dish. Stir remaining ingredients together in frying pan.
Heat to boiling point.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered and 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: cinnamon squash rings
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix brown sugar, milk and egg.
Mix bread crumbs, cornmeal and cinnamon.
Dip squash into egg mixture and coat with bread crumbs.
Place in ungreased baking pan.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until soft.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soups, green chilies and milk together.
Spread Doritos in bottom of well-greased 11 x 13-inch casserole dish. Pour chicken mixture over Doritos.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday log roll
directions: Crush all vanilla wafers into crumbs. Combine vanilla wafer crumbs, chopped pecans and milk together.
Roll into log shape. Then roll the log into confectioners sugar.
Put in wax paper and put in refrigerator for several hours until chilled.

title: cinnamon walnut coffee cake
directions: Use greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 7 ingredients, using only 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Remove 1/4 of this mixture and add chopped walnuts.
Set aside for topping and add 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Add last 4 ingredients to remaining 3/4 of mixture.
Mix well.
(Small lumps are okay.)
Pour this mixture into pan.
Sprinkle topping over batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 33 to 35 minutes.
Topping will be light brown.
Great for breakfast, brunch or dessert.

title: orange cream cheese frosting
directions: In small mixing bowl beat softened cream cheese, margarine or butter and peel until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy and of spreading consistency.
If mixture is too thick, add 1 to 2 teaspoons milk.
Spread on cool cake.

title: lemonade stand pie
directions: Beat lemonade for 30 seconds in large bowl.
Gradually spoon in ice cream, blending well.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Freeze until ready to eat.

title: beef skillet fiesta
directions: Brown meat in oil over high heat in skillet, leaving meat in coarse chunks.
Add onion, reduce heat to medium heat and cook until onion is tender, but not browned.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, corn and bouillon.
Bring to boil.
Stir in green peppers.
Boil again.
Stir in rice, remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Ready to serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Blend butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, then add raisins, nuts, water and pumpkin.
Blend well.
Sift dry ingredients and add, beating well.
Pour into two large bread pans (greased). Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Use toothpick to check for doneness.
Delicious with cream cheese frosting.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Cream oil, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients, then strawberries.
Put in three loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.
Very moist.

title: chicken and corn chili
directions: Heat oil in large heavy pot.
Add garlic, green peppers and onion.
Saute 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add chili powder, cumin and cayenne pepper.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes; mash with spoon.
Add broth.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and simmer for 5 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Stir in salt.

title: southern praline pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour and salt together.
Add the egg, then the lemon juice, raisins and buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle the Praline Topping evenly over filling.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Cool.

title: corn oysters
directions: Place corn in bowl.
Stir in egg yolks, salt, pepper and flour; mix well.
Fold in egg whites gently.
Heat shortening in large skillet.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot fat.
Brown on both sides.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in a crock-pot, stirring occasionally.
Brown sausage in skillet and drain.
Add tomatoes and cooked sausage to melted cheese.
Turn crock-pot on low heat and keep cheese from sticking.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: apple pie
directions: Place oven rack in lowest position.
Heat to 425°.
Mix brown sugar, flour and spices in a large bowl.
Add apples and lemon juice.
Toss gently to mix and coat.
Spread on pie crust in pie plate, mounding apples in center.
Put remaining crust over pie and seal edges.
Brush pie with egg.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Slit top of crust for steam to escape.
Bake 20 minutes.
Reduce oven to 375° and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer, until crust is golden brown and fruit is tender.
If topping browns too quickly, drape a piece of foil loosely over pie.
Serve warm.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker pieces with melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, eggs and 2 sticks butter; beat for 15 minutes, no less!
Put egg mixture on cracker crust.
Put layer of sliced bananas on mixture.
Put pineapple on bananas.
Cover all with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with walnuts and decorate with cherries. Refrigerate for several hours.
Best when made a day ahead and refrigerated overnight.

title: chicken curry
directions: Fry bacon crisp; set aside.
Retain 1 tablespoon bacon grease. Add celery, onion and garlic to grease.
Stir and cook for several minutes.
Add flour and stir until flour begins to cook. Add milk, broth, applesauce, ketchup and curry powder to make a sauce.
When sauce begins to thicken, crumble bacon and add bacon and chicken to sauce.
Heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix flour, mayonnaise, milk and sugar.
Pour into 12 cup muffin pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli-n-cheese
directions: Steam broccoli for approximately 20 minutes.
Melt cheese and half and half in saucepan.
Pour over cooked broccoli.
Mix in crushed cracker crumbs.
Add fresh ground pepper throughout.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium heat. Add flour; cook and stir 10-15 minutes or until flour mixture is deep golden brown. Add onion, bell pepper, carrots, celery and garlic; cook and stir 5 minutes. Stir in broth, clam juice and salt; bring tot a boil. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in shrimp, red pepper and pepper sauce; simmer 6-8 minutes or until shrimp are opaque. Ladles into eight shallow bowls; top each with 1/2 cup rice. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Chill until like syrup.
Fold in 1/2 pint whipped cream.
Break cake in small pieces.
Place cake in pan, then Jell-O mix.
Layer until all is used.
Top with whipped cream.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter.
Add peanut butter and chocolate chips, stirring until smooth. Pour over whole box of cereal tossing to coat. Cool.
Add powdered sugar and toss to coat.

title: peach apricot hot sip
directions: Combine ingredients in Dutch oven.
Heat to boil.
Let stand 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Cool Whip.
Beat one minute at lowest speed.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill about three hours.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: pan-fried pork cutlets
directions: Flatten each slice of pork to about 1/3-inch thickness by pounding between sheets of waxed paper; set aside.
In pie pan, combine flour, salt and pepper.
In small bowl, stir together egg and milk.
In pie pan, combine bread crumbs and paprika.
Coat each slice of pork with flour mixture.
Dip floured slices into egg mixture, then coat with bread crumb mixture.

title: festive ham spread
directions: Combine ham, cream cheese, mayonnaise, onions and relish in a small mixing bowl; mix well.
Chill.
Put on serving plate.
Serve with crackers.

title: pie crust
directions: With a knife, cut first 4 ingredients until mixed well.
Beat the egg really well and spread over the dough, the vinegar over the egg and then the 7-Up.
Take a fork or spoon and mix well together. Roll, with your hands, into a ball or log.
Wrap and put in refrigerator to cool.
(It's easier to work with when cold.)
Makes 2-9 inch pie crusts.
(Not the deep dish kind.)

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Beat with mixer in bowl, the brown sugar, white sugar, oil, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
In a separate large bowl, mix the flour, salt, baking soda, coconut, oatmeal, cornflakes and chocolate chips.
Combine and mix.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cut in shortening.
Heat buttermilk to lukewarm; add yeast and dissolve.
Mix with flour mixture and knead 20 to 30 strokes.
Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut and put one layer in pan and butter top.
Place another cut biscuit on top and butter.
Let rise in a warm place two hours.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine; mix well.
Add sugar and eggs; beat well.
Fold in flour and salt.
Heat waffle iron to medium temperature.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, four at a time.
Bake 1 minute, no longer.
Remove with fork.
Frost with any frosting. You may substitute 12 tablespoons cocoa and 4 tablespoons oil for baking chocolate.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Brown both sides of pork chops; season with garlic and onion. Use enough long grain rice to feed total group; cook until done. In a Pam sprayed pan, place browned chops. After rice is cooked, drain; return to kettle.
Mix in the jar of salsa.
(Amount of salsa depends on servings of rice.
Rice should be moist.)
Place a slice of raw onion on each chop.
Place rice mixture over each chop; let it fall around the meat.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until chops are tender.

title: rockie mount cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Finely chop together the raisins, walnuts, coconut and dates with a food processor.
Then add the milk, water and sugar (can add more sugar to your taste). Cook on medium heat 15 minutes, stirring often.
Then turn heat down to low for 5 minutes.
Put on cake layers while still warm.

title: nanaw's turkey hash
directions: Brown onions and potatoes in oil until soft, but not done.
Add turkey and other ingredients.
Cover and simmer approximately 1 hour.
Nanaw did not actually measure; she used leftover turkey and seasoned to taste.
Might have to add a little water or more cream if necessary.
This was our favorite after Thanksgiving and Christmas!

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix uncooked sausage, cheese and Bisquick together.
Mix it up really good, then start rolling out your sausage balls.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll out medium-size sausage balls.

title: beef enchiladas casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease.
Add spices, salt, comino, garlic and black pepper; stir in onions, tomato sauce and water.
Let simmer over medium heat for about 10 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and cool until lukewarm. Soft yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add to first mixture; add eggs.
Add flour.
Knead.
Put in bowl and grease top.
Let rise until double.
Make into rolls and bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook the fryer in water with the onion until done. (Use enough water to have 4 cups broth.) Cool. Take chicken off bone. Cook the noodles until done; rinse. Put into large baking dish or pan. Add chicken and broth, chicken soup, mushroom soup and sour cream. Mix all together. Add salt and pepper to taste. (You can mix in large bowl and then pour in pan to bake.) Cut the bread into cubes with scissors. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° until golden brown and not too soupy.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Beat mixture well until blended.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake for 1 hour or until crust forms on top.
Serves 8.

title: grandma's oatmeal cake
directions: Combine the oats, oleo and boiling water; let stand 20 minutes.
Add sugars and eggs.
Sift together the flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Combine.
Add to the first mixture and stir until mixed.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook chicken until done.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish (sprayed with non stick spray).
Mix melted butter and cereal together and put on top of casserole.
Bake in oven for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: hot chili beans
directions: Brown meat, onion, pepper, chili powder, salt and garlic salt. Then add crushed tomatoes.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with milk and corn bread.

title: chocolate chipper champs
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour, baking soda and salt. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, melted butter, salt and egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in lemon juice and peel.
Add milk, beating slowly.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in.
Bake pie shell in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Pour in filling.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until filling is firm.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Scald milk in a double boiler.
Using rotary beater, mix in sugar, flour, salt and cocoa.
When this is mixed well, add eggs and mix well again.
Add butter and mix well.
Let cool and add vanilla; mix well for the last time.

title: elaine's italian chicken
directions: Soak chicken pieces in beaten eggs for at least one hour. Shake in bag with bread crumbs to coat.
Brown in skillet with butter.
Place in one layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place mushrooms on top and sliced cheese on top of mushrooms.
Pour in enough broth to coat bottom of pan (may be frozen at this point).
Thaw and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
I usually cover for a while and uncover 15 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: In a food processor, process garlic, mayonnaise, lemon juice and worcestershire sauce until smooth. Add olive oil and 2 Tbsp. cheese; blend just to combine. Toss lettuce with dressing until evenly coated. Divide on plates; top with garlic croutons and remaining Parmesan cheese.

title: french dressing(salad)
directions: Place ingredients in jar and mix.
Can be put in blender to chop onion.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Heat an 8-inch cast-iron skillet 5 minutes in a 400° oven. Combine all ingredients, stirring until moist.
Remove skillet from oven and spray with Pam.
Pour batter into hot skillet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs, then bananas and sour milk.
Sift flour, soda and salt together, then add to banana mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spanish rice casserole(a filling, easy recipe that's easy to make and kids like.)
directions: Cook rice in water with salt.
Bring to boil and remove from heat.
Let set, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir a few times. Saute chuck.
Drain excess fat and return to frypan.
Add salt and pepper.
Add onion and green pepper.
Mix.
Then add tomato soup and mix well.
Pour over rice (when done) in casserole dish. Blend well and serve with hot rolls or soft bread sticks.

title: sourdough pretzels
directions: Break pretzels and spread on baking pan. Pour all mixed ingredients over pretzels and mix well. Bake at 250° for 8 minutes. Take out and stir/mix again. Bake for an additional 7 minutes.

title: lin thomas' sourdough loaves
directions: In a large bowl, stir together sugar, salt, yeast and six cups of flour.
In a 2-quart saucepan on medium heat, heat the yogurt and 2/3 cup of water until very warm (125° to 130°).
Stir into dry ingredients.
Mix until blended and ball forms.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth, about 10 minutes. Cover and let rest for 10 minutes.

title: old-fashioned chocolate candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk and chocolate and boil to soft ball stage. Take off heat and stir in margarine and vanilla.
Pour into buttered pans.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of the meat mixture, chips and cheese in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Repeat layers. Bake for 20 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa, eggs and milk.
Cook until thick. Pour into already cooked pie crust.
Beat egg whites with 4 tablespoons sugar. Pour over pies and bake until brown.

title: triple cheese pizza
directions: Layer pizza crust of your choice with pesto, cheese and tomatoes.
Season with pepper and oregano.
Top with Parmesan and Mozzarella.
Bake at 500° for 10 minutes.

title: always tender pie crust
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together with a fork.
Blend next 3 ingredients together; add water mixture.
Roll out pie crusts. Makes 3 pie crusts.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Microwave almond bark and chocolate chips; stir well with spoon to blend. Add peanuts and stir. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Let set until firm.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Mix all ingredients (except butter) and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter. Cover with top crust.

title: stand up and cheer cake
directions: Bake cake.
Punch holes with toothpick.
Drain juice from pineapple. Pour over cake.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and pineapple. Spread over cake.
Mix instant pudding as usual. Spread over cake.
Then spread Cool Whip.
Nuts and cherries can be added.

title: clay's shrimp mousse
directions: Mix soup and cream cheese over low heat.
Add gelatin and let cool. Mix rest of ingredients and chill in bowl or mold 4 to 6 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Put liquid from potatoes and water in saucepan.
Add thickening; heat until thick.
Alternate layers of potatoes and apples in baking dish.
Cover with liquid.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lu's roast beef
directions: Place roast in roasting pan. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Place potatoes and carrots around roast. Combine remaining ingredients and 1 soup can of water in blender container.
Process until smooth.
Pour over roast and vegetables.
Bake, covered, at 275° for 3 hours longer or until roast is tender.
You may slice an onion, if you prefer, over the roast.
Yields 6 servings.

title: basic cheesecake(easy, delicious!)
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend on High for 1 minute or 3 minutes with an electric mixer.
Pour into an 8-inch graham cracker
crust, or it is great without a crust as well. Microwave on Low for 19 to 23 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn every 7 minutes until center is almost set.
(Cut through it with a knife to see if it is set.
When knife is clean, it's ready.) Makes 1 (8-inch) cheesecake.

title: dry roasted peanut candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips, oleo and Eagle Brand milk together. Stir in nuts and marshmallows.
Pour into greased pan, cool and serve.

title: creamy glaze
directions: Heat margarine in saucepan until melted.
Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until smooth and of desired consistency.
Spread on cool cake.
Sprinkle top with peppermint candies.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes.
Turn temperature down to 350 degrees, and bake for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in greased loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves (can freeze).

title: scalloped potatoes and carrots
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and parsley and cook until onion is tender.
Blend in flour, salt and dill.
Stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly until sauce thickens slightly and comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine the above in a microwave bowl. Cook on high for 4 minutes. Stir and cook for 3 more minutes.
Stir and add 1 Tbsp. margarine and 1 tsp. vanilla extract.
Cook for 2-1/2 more minutes.
Remove from microwave and add 1 tsp. baking soda.
Stir.
Will foam up very quickly.
Pour onto a greased surface.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Peel and slice.
Add sliced onion (optional).
Fry bacon until crispy.
Remove from pan.
To the bacon fat, add the butter and flour.
Stir and add vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Let come to a boil and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle bacon cubes on top of salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Cover with water and begin to boil about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add soups, bell pepper and water as needed.
Salt and pepper to taste and add 1 tablespoon of sugar.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Marinate overnight fruit in poppy seed dressing.

title: baked chicken
directions: Line baking dish with chipped beef.
Roll each chicken breast in a strip of bacon.
Combine sour cream and soup.
Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
Pour the sauce over the chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: easy stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut off stems and hollow out mushroom tops.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Add enough gravy (jar or canned gravy is okay) just to hold meat together.
Coat inside of each mushroom cap with sour cream.
Spoon in meat mixture and top with shredded cheese.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet, uncovered, at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on warm platter.

title: easy fettuccine
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil in skillet on low heat until golden brown.
Stir in processed cheese spread, milk and Parmesan cheese until melted.
Add fettuccine; mix lightly.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash and grind the cranberries.
Pare and chop or grind the apples.
Add pineapple, nuts and sugar.
Dissolve the jello in the hot water and add the cold water.
When cool, add the salad mixture and allow to congeal.
Serves 6.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in greased baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes; not too well done.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning together. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with foil and refrigerate several hours.
Top with onions, tomatoes, lettuce, cheese and olives. Serve with taco chips using chips to scoop out dip.

title: double dipped spicy chicken
directions: Heat 1 1/2-inches vegetable oil in a deep skillet over medium-high heat. A cube of bread should brown in a 40 count when oil is ready. Set out 3 disposable pie tins. Mix flour with paprika, poultry seasoning, cayenne and allspice. Divide seasoned flour between 2 tins. Pour buttermilk into a tin. Line up tins as such: flour, buttermilk and then flour. Season chicken with salt and pepper. Coat chicken pieces in flour, then buttermilk, then a second coating in flour. Cook chicken 6 minutes on each side, until deep golden brown and firm. Drain chicken on paper bags and cool.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain excess water.
Add chicken soup, can of milk and Cheez Whiz.
Simmer until Cheez Whiz is melted and soup is heated through.
Eat!

title: indiana picnic cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, oleo and nuts together; set 1 cup aside.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in 10 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the 1 cup on top and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Needs no frosting.

title: hundred dollar cake
directions: No milk, no shortening, no eggs.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, cocoa and milk in heavy saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on wax paper with spoon.

title: orange cream cheese cups
directions: Drain pineapple, add hot water to syrup to make 1 1/2 cups. Bring to a boil, then add gelatin and stir to dissolve.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Bring stock or water to boil.
Add all ingredients.
Cook until done.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Put in a bowl.
Let soak 2 hours.
Drain well; don't wash. Add 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup white vinegar.
Mix well.
Pack and freeze.

title: maucia's coffee can bread
directions: Put the yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and warm water in mixer bowl and stir.
Cover; let stand until bubbles form (about 15 minutes). Add flour, milk, 3 tablespoons sugar and salt to the yeast mixture after bubbles have formed.
Mix well! Divide into 2 parts and drop into well-greased one-pound coffee cans.
Punch dough down with a spoon to remove air.
Place greased coffee can lids on cans.
Let stand at room temperature until lids pop off (about 1 hour).
Remove lids and grease top of dough to make better crust. Bake in cans at 350° for 45 minutes, until crust is brown.

title: scallops supreme
directions: Coat scallops with seasoned bread crumbs that have been mixed with 2 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper.
Mix butter with 4 cloves of pressed garlic and 4 tablespoons olive oil.
Put butter mixture in frying pan and let get hot.
Fry scallops 4 minutes per side until browned.
Add 1 1/2 shots sherry into pan.
Cook a few minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon champagne punch
directions: Mix juices and water.
Chill, covered.
Before serving, add ginger ale and sparkling water and pour over ice cubes in punch bowl.
Pour chilled champagne over punch and stir gently. Yields 50 servings.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add enough water to make 1 cup; heat. Then add box of Jell-O. Mix well. Let cool. Add 7-Up and refrigerate until partly set. Add cranberries and pineapple. Mix together and pour in 9 x 12 dish. Refrigerate and let set, then frost.

title: easy crock-pot mac and cheese
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with 2 cups of cheese. Pour into crock-pot. Sprinkle rest of cheese on top. Close lid. Cook on low for 3 hours. Do not remove lid during cooking time.

title: honey lemon dressing
directions: In a bowl, whisk together zest, lemon juice and honey until combined well, then whisk in buttermilk, yogurt or sour cream, oil, vanilla and a pinch of salt.
Makes 3/4 cup.
Excellent over fruit.

title: chocolate sunday pie
directions: Soak for 5 minutes the envelope of gelatin and 1/4 cup water; set aside.
Combine in heavy saucepan the milk, salt, 4 tablespoons sugar and egg yolks; cook until custard thickens.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add the vanilla.
Cool; fold in 2 large egg whites, beaten until soft peaks form.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pour into crust.
Top with whipped cream.
Top with grated Hershey bar.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions with butter.
Cook rice (do not use Minute rice) and drain.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz, broccoli (thawed and uncooked) and water chestnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot completely through.

title: melt-in-your-mouth nut strudel
directions: Beat the cream cheese and margarine in mixer bowl with electric mixer until well combined.
Add flour; mix well.
Shape into ball.
Cover; chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: blue mountain barbecue sauce
directions: In a medium non-aluminum saucepan, combine all ingredients. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 8 to 10 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Let cool before using.

title: five hour beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large Dutch oven (no need to brown meat).
Cover and
bake
4 to 5 hours at 275° or cook in crock-pot.	Delicious and easy make ahead meal.

title: chocolate dump cake
directions: Bring to a boil the butter, cocoa and water.
Remove from heat; add flour, buttermilk, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Ice while hot.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken. Debone and remove skin.

title: chow hound
directions: Add ground meat, onion and bell pepper; cook until meat is brown.
At the same time be cooking rice until tender.
Boil shrimp.
Scramble eggs in another pan.
Add all ingredients together; mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve.
You can make as much as you need.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: *If you use more than 4 chicken breasts, use 2 cans soup and 1 pint sour cream.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Simmer squash until just tender; drain.
Combine sour cream, melted butter, cheese, salt and paprika.
Stir mixture over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in egg yolk.
Next, stir squash into mixture.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: cooky surprises
directions: In bowl beat together butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs, water and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add to butter mixture with oats, Krispies and candy.

title: mock pink champagne
directions: Combine sugar and water in sauce pan; simmer uncovered, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves (approximately 3 minutes).
Pour mixture in punch bowl; and mix with remaining ingredients except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Add a Maraschino cherry to each glass and a twist of lemon peel.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add juice and cheese.
Cook until cheese has melted.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: spring pasta salad
directions: Mix juices, garlic, vinegar, honey, mustard, basil and salt. Combine with all other ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Stir well. Chill until serving time.

title: pennsylvania corn pone
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat egg; add oil and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Bake in a greased 9-inch cast-iron skillet 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix all together and bake in muffin pans (with papers).

title: banana bread with dates
directions: Mix mayo and sugar well.
Add bananas to sifted flour, soda, walnuts and dates.
Mix and pour into well greased and floured pans (2 med. pans or 5 sm. foil pans).
Bake at 350° for about 45 min. for sm. pans and 1 hour for med. pans.
Cool in pans 5 min. then turn out on rack to cool.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix
sugar,
flour and pineapple along with juice.
Cook until thick; cool.
Slice bananas in pie shells, sprinkle with nuts. Pour
pineapple
mixture
over
this
and
sprinkle with coconut. Spread top with Cool Whip.	Chill and serve.

title: strata
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Butter one side.
Place buttered side down in 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over the bread, then lay 1 pound cooked sausage on the cheese.
Add Monterey Jack cheese over the sausage.

title: apricot bavarian
directions: Drain apricots and puree.
Sprinkle gelatin over top.
Let set until softened, about 5 minutes.
Bring to boiling; add powdered sugar.
Cool, then add in a package of whipped topping.
Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: doughnuts
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add milk and beat thoroughly.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Toss dough onto a floured board and roll out until it is one third of an inch thick.
Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep fat, turning to brown both sides.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Dredge beef cubes with flour.
Heat Dutch oven or pressure cooker.
Add oil and brown meat well.
Add remaining ingredients. (If meat sticks to pan, add a little of the vinegar and scrape it.) Bring to boil.
Lower heat and cook 30 to 40 minutes or pressure cook 20 minutes.
Serve with broad egg noodles and a green vegetable.
This is even tastier reheated.

title: mushroom wild rice
directions: In a large saucepan, bring water, wild rice, butter and 1/2 t salt to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Stir in brown rice and cover and simmer 25-30 minutes longer until rice is tender.
While rice is cooking, brown bacon in a large skillet until crisp. Remove bacon and drain, leaving 2 T of the bacon drippings in the pan.
Saute the mushrooms, onions, peppers and celery in the drippings until they are tender. Stir in broth and remaining salt and bring mixture to a boil.
Combine the cornstarch and cold water until smooth and stir into the mushroom mixture.
Cook 2 minutes until thickened then stir in almonds and bacon pieces.
Drain the rice and add mushroom mixture.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and let stand overnight or at least 12 hours.
Drain and wash twice; set aside and prepare sauce.

title: taco seasoning(healthy mixes u-make)
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in airtight container in a cool, dry place.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash and trim the ends of the zucchini. Cut in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp. Finely chop pulp.
In a mixing bowl, combine pulp, ground beef, bread crumbs, parsley, Parmesan cheese, onion and egg. Add seasonings.
Fill zucchini shells with meat mixture. Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine tomato soup and water.
Pour over zucchini. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: raspberry filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until fluffy. Add egg, milk and vanilla. Beat well. Mix dry ingredients together, except oats. Add dry ingredients with oats to creamed mixture. Mix well. Chill 1 hour.

title: beef marinade
directions: Place beef in marinade and refrigerate for 2 to 3 days.

title: meat sauce for meat loaf
directions: Mix together and pour over meat loaf before baking.

title: brittles
directions: Heat butter and sugar to boiling; boil 5 minutes.
Line 8 x 11-inch jelly roll pan with foil.
Place crackers in 1 layer and pour batter mixture over them.
Place in a 350° oven until crackers rise.
Melt chocolate chips in microwave and spread over crackers.
Add nuts.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: applesauce cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cucumber and yogurt salad
directions: Peel cucumber and slice very thin.
Mix with mint and salt and pepper to taste in bowl.
Add yogurt; mix gently.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, eggs, cheese and mayonnaise.
Blend in broccoli. Place in lightly greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle on cracker crumbs.
Pat on butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mini smoked beef and cheese sandwich
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread rolls with mustard; fill with meat and Velveeta.
Wrap each sandwich in foil.
Bake 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, blending mixture.
Pour into two 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans and bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until done.
Cool and frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: spicy raisin bars
directions: Heat water and raisins on the stove.
Let cool slightly, then add salad oil or shortening, egg and sugar.
Sift together flour and other dry ingredients and add to the mixture.
Add nuts if desired.
Grease and lightly flour bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
When cool, dust with powdered sugar and cut into bars.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add vinegar to milk to sour it.
Add eggs, butter, milk and raisins to dry ingredients. Knead on floured board or mix with spoon.
Mix until soft dough is formed.
Place in loaf pan or round baking pan.
Bake 55 minutes in 275° oven.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: In
medium saucepan combine butter,
water
and
cocoa. Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In bowl stir together flour,
sugar,
soda and salt.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
By
hand
beat until smooth.
Stir into hot cocoa mixture.
Mix
well.
Pour
into greased
and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch
pan.
Bake
at 400° for 20 minutes.
Frost while warm.
Cut when cool.

title: chicken essex
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight. When ready to bake, remove foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: glogg
directions: Tie spices into a piece of white cheesecloth.
Simmer spices and fruit in a pan (not aluminum pan, I use a porcelain pot). Cover with 2-inches of water.
Cook until fruit is soft.
Add wine and bring to a boil.
Add brandy.
Shut off heat; ignite surface with a match.
Burn for 15 seconds.
Cover with a lid.

title: topping for angel food cake slices
directions: Combine condensed milk and lemon juice in a bowl and stir with spoon to mix.
Add pineapple and oranges into mixture.
Blend in Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to use.
Place about 1/2 to 1 cup on top of angel food cake slice when ready to serve.
Great dessert for summer!

title: chicken crunch
directions: Reserve a few onions for topping.
Mix remaining ingredients together and place in baking dish.
Top with onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: midge's cheese krispies
directions: Grate cheese in large mixing bowl.
Put oleo in bowl with cheese and let stand until soft.
Cream well.
Add flour, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll in small balls; place on cookie sheet and press with fork.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Watch carefully after 15 minutes.
Do not brown, but should be crisp.

title: penna dutch white coconut cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Beat well; add yolks.
Sift dry ingredients and add milk alternately.
Fold in beaten egg whites; add coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in oven with door open.
Grease two 8-inch round cake pans and flour.

title: yam and apple casserole
directions: Cook yams in water until almost tender, 25 minutes.
Cool and remove the skins.
Cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Pare and core apples; cut each in 6 rings.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, meal, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken parts evenly, covering well with flour mixture.
Put in large frying pan in 1 cup hot grease. Constantly turn until chicken is good and brown. Reduce heat and let cook for 10 to 12 minutes. Serve.

title: french bread(makes 6 loaves)
directions: Sprinkle yeast in 1/2 cup water in bowl.
Mix sugar and salt in 4 cups water.
Add shortening and yeast and mix well.
Add flour; mix well.
Knead until not sticky.
Place in greased bowl. Turn to grease top.
Cover.
Punch down well every 10 minutes for 5 times. Let rest, covered, 10 minutes.
Shape into loaves by rolling out in rectangular shape.
Roll into loaves.
Cut diagonal cuts across top.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Work in shortening and lukewarm water to make a soft dough.
Chill in refrigerator.
Roll out dough on floured surface to about 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut into 2 inch squares.
Deep fry in hot shortening at 400° a few at a time.
Brown on each side and drain on paper towel.
Serve hot. To eat, break open and pour in honey or use honey butter.

title: raisin nut cookies
directions: Blend sugar and shortening; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk.
Mix well.
Grind raisins and black walnuts together. Mix to cream mixture.
Mix the dry ingredients with the flour. Add dry mixture to the creamed mixture; mix until well blended. Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes, or until brown.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Split unpeeled squash lengthwise into 2 halves.
Scoop out both of the centers.
Combine hamburg, onion, cottage cheese, garlic and tomato juice.
Pile onto the squash halves.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Arrange in baking pan, uncovered.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cream fudge
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with foil so that foil extends over sides of pan; butter foil.
In large saucepan, combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.

Add pineapple pastry filling and bring to boil again, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add Marshmallow Creme and 1 pound white chocolate coating; blend until smooth.
Add pineapple candy oil and blend. Add Karo syrup and blend.
Pour into prepared pan.
Cool to room temperature.
Score fudge into 36 or 48 squares.
Refrigerate until firm.
Remove fudge from pan by lifting foil; remove foil from fudge.
Using large knife, cut through scored lines.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: buttered crab meat
directions: Combine wine, lemon juice, nutmeg, salt and pepper in a shallow pan and bring to a boil.
Add crab meat and just heat through.
Meanwhile, cream butter, anchovy and egg yolks.
Stir gradually into crab mixture, do not let it boil, and cook gently, stirring all the while, until it is thickened.
Taste to see if more salt and pepper is needed.
Serve very hot in shells or in chafing dish surrounded by sippets.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Prepare bouillon broth.
Beat eggs well.
When broth is hot, but not boiling, pour beaten eggs very slowly into broth, stirring with a fork so eggs string.
Serve warm.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients on low speed until wet.
Continue beating for 4 minutes on medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a Bundt pan.

title: sugar cane-mandarin fruit drink
directions: Mix juices and chill.
Serve over ice with or without ginger ale.
When serving as a punch, cook with Ice Ring (see index for Ice Ring).
Serves 4 to 8.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° in layers.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook mixture until thick, then chill through (may be set in freezer to chill).

title: spanakopita(spinach pita)
directions: Beat eggs; add spinach, onion, leeks, pepper, baking powder, cheeses and 1/4 cup butter and olive oil.
Mix with a tablespoon. Brush a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with melted butter.
Layer with 6 sheets of dough, brushing butter between sheets.
Start spreading 1/2 cup mixture and alternate with one sheet; cover.
Spread mixture evenly.
Do this until you use all of mixture.
Then use 6 sheets to cover top, brushing each sheet with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve.
Can be frozen.

title: cookies for santa
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix sugar, shortening, egg, honey and lemon extract. Stir in remaining ingredients. Roll dough 1/4 inch thick. Use cookie cutters to cut into desired shapes. Place 1 inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake approximately 7 to 8 minutes or until no indentation remains when cookies are touched. Cool cookies and decorate if desired.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for one hour.

title: bacon cheddar puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Bring milk and margarine to boil over medium heat; add flour all at once, stirring constantly, until mixture forms a ball and leaves sides of pan. Remove from heat. Add eggs, one at a time, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth. Add remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonful on greased foil-lined cooked sheet. Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in nuts.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Combine milk, tapioca and sweetener and salt.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add 2 slightly beaten egg yolks.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat (mixture will be thin).
Add vanilla. Beat 2 egg whites to stiff peaks. Gradually fold in hot mixture. Chill.
Serves 8.

title: mexican hot sauce dip
directions: Mix all together in a blender until smooth.
Serve with Doritos.
Makes 1 quart.
Very good on all Mexican food and as a dip.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Blend in sweet potatoes.
Add enough milk to make soft dough.
Knead lightly.
Roll 3/4-inch thick on floured board; cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes, or until brown.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Cook potatoes in skins until tender.
Cool, peel and cut into small pieces.
In saucepan, combine on low heat, 1/4 cup oleo and Cheddar cheese.
Stir until melted.
Blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes.
Put in buttered casserole or baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen or made ahead of time and bake.

title: martha's homemade salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and mix for 1 to 2 minutes. Store in refrigerator.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Heat iron
skillet lightly oiled on top of stove.
Heat, hot. Pour in batter
and
bake at 425° for about 25 minutes or until done.
Test center with toothpick method.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: individual cheesecakes
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and eggs until smooth.
Line muffin tin with aluminum muffin tin liners.
Put a vanilla wafer in each.
Fill with 3/4 cup of cream cheese mixture.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Top with cherry or pineapple topping after cooling them.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.
Yield: 24 individual cheesecakes.

title: finger lickin chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts into strips.
Dip in beaten egg and roll in Ritz crackers.
Brown in skillet of melted butter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together peanut butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar, lemon juice and chocolate chips.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Spoon into crust and chill 3 to 4 hours or freeze.

title: mrs. winter's pineapple cheesecake
directions: Put undrained crushed pineapple into a saucepan.
Mix cornstarch with water to make a paste and stir into pineapple.
Add the sugar and cook the mixture until thickened; cool.

title: mediterranean scallops
directions: Cut pepper in julienne strips. In hot oil, cook garlic briefly.
Add pepper, tomatoes, olives, capers and thyme.
Cook 5 minutes.
Melt butter; add scallops and cook about 3 minutes. Sprinkle lemon juice and basil over and stir briefly.
Spoon tomato mixture on heated plates with scallops over mixture.
Serves 4.

title: quick brownies
directions: Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: "good" cooked chocolate icing
directions: Bring to a boil.
Boil one minute; let cool until thick.
Beat slightly and spread on cake.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Dump flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt to first mixture.
Add milk and vanilla. Place in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake in a covered baking dish with a rack to drain grease.
Place bacon slices on top of meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a preheated oven.
For 2 small loaves, bake 1/2 hour.

title: seven-up dressing
directions: Combine salad dressing and sour cream.
Gradually add Seven-Up mixing until smooth.
Chill.
Serve over vegetables.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichoke hearts and combine with mayonnaise, cheese, garlic salt.
Mix thoroughly and spread into 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: beef toastwich
directions: Brown beef and onion; add flour and hot water and cook 5 minutes.
Add mustard and chili sauce and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve in toasted bun.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the cheese, crackers and margarine together and put into a casserole dish.
On top, cover with the grated cheese and crumble Ritz crackers over the cheese. Drizzle the melted margarine over top and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix the softened cream cheese and sour cream together and spread on a round pan or platter. Cook the hamburger meat like you are making tacos. After hamburger is done, spread it over the sour cream and cream cheese. Then pour the picante sauce over the hamburger and layer the finely chopped tomato, bell pepper and onion over the sauce. Top with cheese. Garnish with jalapenos if desired.

title: frozen banana mousse
directions: Peel and place bananas in heavy plastic bag.
Freeze at least 6 hours.
Remove from freezer and cut each into 5 or 6 pieces.
In the work bowl of a food processor fitted with a metal blade, process banana pieces and remaining ingredients, scraping sides until smooth and creamy.

title: broccoli-spinach bake
directions: Prepare broccoli and spinach as directed on package. Combine these with sour cream and soup mix. Put into a 9 by 13 inch pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°. Just before done, add grated cheese on top. Bake until cheese is melted.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients as for pie crust (no water). Spread mixture on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pare and slice apples.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cover with pie topping.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine all dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks, vanilla, margarine and milk.
Cook on medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue, if desired.
Bake at 400° until meringue is browned.

title: *tigani(fried dough)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Add flour and salt.
Mix with spoon and let rise for 1 hour.
Drop by tablespoons in hot oil (375°). Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Drain on paper towel. Dust with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: honey crunch
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, combine cereal, oats, nuts, cinnamon and salt.
In small saucepan, combine oleo, honey and brown sugar.
Cook over low heat until sugar melts.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Mix until coated.
Spread evenly onto greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Stir twice while cooking. Remove from oven.
Add raisins.
Cool on wax paper-covered cooling rack.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: no fuss chicken
directions: In bowl, combine dressing, preserves and soup mix.
Place chicken in 2 ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch pans.
Top with dressing mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Baste.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes longer or until chicken is done.

title: chile sauce
directions: Mix all except spices and vinegar. Boil 45 minutes. Then add spices. Tie in bag. Cook until thick. Then add vinegar. Boil until desired.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Stir boiling water into jello for 2 minutes. Stir in frozen yogurt until melted. Stir in Cool Whip lite and fruit. Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, then add remaining ingredients.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend with mixer until smooth.
Use as dip or pour over bowl of mixed fruit.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain well.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package and drain; set aside.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients well and put in large casserole dish.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: salami
directions: Knead like bread 5 minutes a day for 3 days.
(Keep it in the refrigerator.)
On the 4th day, shape into 3 rolls; place on your broiler pan in the oven set at 160° and bake for 9 hours.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Cake:
Beat all ingredients of yellow cake, oranges, eggs and oil.
Use 3 greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve the gelatin in the boiling water in a bowl.
Stir in the undrained pineapple and pie filling.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Chill for 1 hour or until set.
Beat the cream cheese and sugar in a mixer bowl until fluffy.
Add the sour cream, pecans and vanilla.
Spread over the congealed layer.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 8 servings.

title: strudel
directions: Press 1 can of rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Spread over rolls.
Top with second can of rolls.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with powdered sugar icing.

title: basic omelet
directions: Cook butter in 9-inch glass pie plate at low 2 minutes.
Turn plate to coat with butter.
Meanwhile, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie plate.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook at Medium 2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until omelet is almost set; stir after 1 minute.
Let stand covered 2 minutes with spatula.
Loosen edges of omelet from plate.
Fold into thirds to serve.

title: golden bars
directions: Mix Cheerios, nuts and coconut in large bowl; set aside.
Mix in saucepan sugar, corn syrup and milk together and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally to 236° or until soft ball stage. Remove and pour syrup mixture over Cheerios; mix well.
Put in a buttered 9-inch pan and pat.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: medley marinade(vegetable salad)
directions: Combine vegetables.
Mix vinegar, sugar and oil.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Chill 24 hours.
Drain before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: three-day baked brisket(makes 4 to 6  pounds)
directions: Sprinkle uncooked brisket with liquid smoke, garlic salt and lemon or lime juice. Wrap in heavy foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in cookie sheet, pat down to cover pan. Bake at 325° until golden brown, cool.
Blend together cream cheese, Ranch dressing and mayonnaise.
Spread on the baked cool crust.
Top with veggies of your choice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, onion and bell pepper in a large bowl.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook and stir onion and garlic in hot margarine until tender (not browned).
Add remaining ingredients, except cream, and bring to a boil.
Carefully pour half the soup into blender and puree.
Repeat with remaining soup.
Stir in cream and stir. Makes about 10 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
In medium bowl stir together spinach, sour cream, mayo, soup mix, water chestnuts and onions. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Makes 3 cups.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat sauce to a boil.
Pour over ribs or beef.

title: no sugar fresh fruit ambrosia
directions: Combine orange juice, club soda and banana in blender and puree until smooth.
Pour over fresh fruit.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cardamon.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve. Sprinkle with coconut before serving.

title: cheese straws
directions: Blend soft butter with flour; add grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Blend thoroughly.
Fill cookie press 1/2 full.
Use star attachment and press out in long strips.
Bake in 425° oven until very lightly brown, then cut in 2-inch strips.
Cool and store in airtight container.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen 2-inch cheese straws.

title: fat-free banana bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients until smooth; set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients and add to first mixture.
Put in a loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes until done in 350° oven.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine butter, heavy cream and cream cheese. Simmer until all is melted and mix well. Add the Parmesan cheese and garlic powder. Simmer this for at least 20 minutes on low (or the longer the better). You may want to season with a little salt and pepper.

title: fruit cake
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and baking powder 4 times.
Roll nuts and fruit in part of flour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300° in tube pan.

title: carrot and marshmallow salad
directions: Peel carrots.
Shred with a coarse shredder into a bowl.
Add marshmallows, pineapple, raisins and coconut.
Toss lightly to mix. Combine mayonnaise with mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Combine all ingredients in large kettle.
Bring to full boil. Strain in cheesecloth into large bowl.
Add 1 bottle of Certo. Return
to
kettle
and
bring
to
full
boil.
Cook, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add 3 or 4 drops green
or
red
food coloring.
Pour into small jelly glasses (jelly
tends
to sugar after opening) and pour melted paraffin on top.

title: ginger-lime punch
directions: Pour concentrates into punch bowl.
Add ginger; chill at least 2 hours to blend flavors.
Add cold water and ice.
Pour ginger ale down side of bowl.
Trim with citrus floaters.
Serves 20.

title: chicken and dumplings - made easy
directions: Heat chicken, water and chicken soup until hot. Make dumplings out of Bisquick and milk. Roll out and cut into 1-inch squares and drop into chicken mixture.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put into buttered casserole.
Mix crackers and butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake until bubbly and starts to brown.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and raisins; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack. Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in oleo.
Cook broccoli thoroughly; drain.
Mix well with celery and onion mixture.
Add rice, cheese and soups.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Take meat from bones and crumble up.
Layer bowl with Doritos or Corn Chips.
Place chicken on top of chips.
Combine liquids to form sauce and pour over meat. Sprinkle cheese over sauce.
Repeat with second layer of ingredients and cover with chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for a few minutes.

title: zucchini freezer jam
directions: Cook zucchini for 12 to 15 minutes until clear (no water), stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice, pineapple and sugar.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Add gelatin and stir. Put into freezer containers and freeze.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook and stir green pepper and mushrooms in margarine in saucepan over medium heat. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in milk, broth and reserved mushroom liquid.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, for 1 minute. Stir in chicken and pimentos.
Heat until hot.

title: poor man's steak
directions: In bowl, mix ground chuck, green peppers, onions, celery, eggs, crushed saltines, salt and pepper.
Make into small patties, fry until done.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour soup, undiluted, over meat patties.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Place in a casserole dish. Sprinkle olives over hamburger.
Mix together eggs, tomato sauce, evaporated milk and enchilada sauce mix until well blended.
Pour mixture over hamburger.
Sprinkle corn chips over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until mixture is set.
Add Cheddar cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: summer lasagna
directions: Combine tomato sauce, onion, basil, salt, pepper and oregano in small mixing bowl; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta, Mozzarella and parsley.
Set aside.
Peel zucchini and cut off ends.
Slice zucchini lengthwise into strips.
Arrange strips in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High, 6 to 8 minutes or until fork-tender, rearranging after half the time.
Drain liquid; place zucchini on paper towels to absorb excess moisture.
Cool slightly.
Layer 4 to 6 of the strips in the bottom of baking dish.
Reserve 6 strips for second layer. Spread Ricotta mixture over zucchini.
Layer with sliced tomatoes. Spread half of tomato sauce mixture over tomatoes; top with zucchini slices.
Pour remaining sauce over zucchini and sprinkle with Parmesan.
Reduce power to 50% (Medium).
Microwave, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes or until zucchini is tender and mixture is hot in center.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple. Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: moore's brunswick stew(from the 30's)
directions: Cook chicken and pork separately until done.
Cool and cut up or grind the lean meat.
Cook the stew in the broth from the hen. Use a large pot and cook all of the following.

title: strawberry cream cake
directions: Cut about 1-inch of top of cake.
Then cut 1-inch tunnel out of center of ring.
Mix half of Cool Whip with the strawberries and fill the tunnel you cut in the cake.
Use the rest of the Cool Whip to ice the cake after setting top back on.

title: shrimp appetizer squares
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Press dough into 13 x 9 rectangle on greased baking sheet. Bake for 5 to 10 minutes or until light golden brown. In 10-inch skillet, heat butter until sizzling; add all remaining ingredients except cheese. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisply tender. Drain. Top baked crust with 1/2 of cheese. Spoon shrimp and vegetable mixture evenly over cheese. Top with remaining cheese. Continue baking for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: pa dutch chicken pie
directions: Line 8 or 9-inch tin with pie dough.
Fill with chicken.
Top with diced egg, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup gravy.
Cover pie with dough; flute edges.
Bake about 25 minutes in 400° oven. Serve reserved gravy with the baked pie.

title: easy devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour with soda, salt and sugar.
Stir butter to soften. Add flour mixture, milk and vanilla.
Mix to moisten flour.
Then beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer or 300 vigorous strokes by hand, scraping bowl occasionally.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 70 minutes.

title: fresca punch
directions: For pink punch, substitute cranberry juice for pineapple juice.

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking dish. In a medium saucepan melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Add onions and saute until browned.
Combine eggs, cream, cheese, caraway seed, mustard, salt and pepper.
Layer half the potatoes in bottom of dish.
Cover with 1/3 of egg mixture; then add onions, sausage and remaining potatoes.
Pour rest of egg mixture over potatoes.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown. Serves 4.

title: bible cake
