directions: Grease and flour 3 (8-inch) or 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into pans.
Bake 8-inch pans for 35 minutes and 9-inch pans for 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: near olive garden dressing
directions: In a 2-cup jar with a tight-fitting lid, combine salad dressing, egg, Parmesan, Romano and parsley.
Seal jar and shake to blend.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: crumbly top apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Add to apple slices.
Arrange apples in pie crust.
Blend brown sugar and flour.
Cut in margarine with a pastry blender or fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, instant milk, onion, salt, pepper, Worcestershire and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Press onto bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle with 3/4 cup shredded cheese.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over cheese.
Spread mashed potatoes over top.
Dot with remaining cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted (about 5 minutes).

title: peanut cracker jacks
directions: Mix together popped corn and peanuts in a very large bowl or roaster pan.
Keep warm in a 250° oven.
Melt margarine in a heavy two-quart saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly, using medium heat. Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Quickly pour over popcorn-peanut mixture, tossing until kernels and nuts are well coated.
Spread out in shallow baking pan or large sheet.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring once every 15 minutes, then remove from the oven.
Turn out on aluminum foil to cool.
Break into pieces. Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 3 quarts and stores well in a gallon jar.
Mixture does not have crisp texture until cooled.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters.
In a bag, put sugar and cinnamon.
Shake biscuits in bag.
Layer biscuits into greased tube pan.
Sprinkle nuts between layers, if desired.
Melt brown sugar and butter.
Boil for 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Peel, core and quarter apples.
Bring to a boil water, sugar and margarine.
Roll out biscuits.
Cut each in half.
Wrap quarter apple with half biscuit.
Place in a baking dish.
Pour hot water, sugar and margarine mixture over each dumpling. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 dumplings.

title: poor mans whipped cream
directions: Beat all together, then add by tablespoon 2/3 cup hot milk while beating at high speed.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In bottom of 9 X 13 pan that has been greased only, sprinkle chopped nuts and coconut.
Mix chocolate cake according to package and pour over the nuts.
Mix stick of oleo and cream cheese until smooth then add powdered sugar and vanilla, mix well.
Spoon cheese mixture over the cake batter, trying to stay away from the sides of pan.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Melt gelatin in water.
Heat soup and let cool.
Add all other ingredients and pour into greased mold.
Best when refrigerated overnight.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Finely chop onion in shortening and brown.
Remove onion from skillet.
Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Mix ground beef, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Roll in flour.
Fry in onion skillet until brown.
Remove meat balls.

title: oven scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Pour over frozen hash browns in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix together sour cream, soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Spread over potatoes.
Melt second stick of margarine. Mix with crushed cornflakes.
Spread over top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered, then 20 minutes uncovered.

title: lumpia
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg roll wrappers in food processor.
Wrap 1 tablespoon of mix in each egg roll wrapper. Wrap according to directions on package.
Use a flour paste to seal.
Deep fat fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Pour mixture into casserole dish or pie pan (this is crust).
Add green beans next.
Spread the mashed potatoes on top for the meringue.

title: decadent caramel corn
directions: Place pecans and popped corn in large shallow pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Melt butter in 1-quart saucepan over low heat; stir in brown sugar and honey.
Increase heat to medium and bring mixture to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil mixture gently for 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture over nuts/popcorn; stir until coated.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: graham's vegetable soup
directions: Cook steak in frying pan with a little butter.
Put diced potatoes in a boiler and boil them until almost done.
Drain potatoes.
In large boiler, add cooked meat and butter, potatoes and the rest of ingredients.
Cook over low heat for about 2 hours. Serve with bran muffins.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on.
Let cool and peel.
Grate on cheese grater.
Mix sour cream, margarine and potatoes.
Add onions, salt, pepper and half the grated cheese.
Mix all ingredients and place in a casserole dish with cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cover with 1 cup (remaining) grated cheese and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: baked beef and cabbage
directions: Coarsely shred cabbage to measure 5 or 6 cups.
Spread half in a large buttered casserole or roasting pan.
Heat oil in frypan and add beef, onion, rice, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, but do not brown (about 10minutes). Spoon meat mixture over cabbage.
Top with remaining cabbage. Heat tomatoes with water and bouillon cube to boiling point.
Pour over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cabbage is tender.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, egg, creamed corn and milk.
Add 1 lb. cooked (not browned) hamburger meat, cheese, onion and peppers.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a hot oiled iron skillet and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 425 to 450°.
Serves 6-8.

title: fluffy oatmeal pancakes
directions: Combine buttermilk and rolled oats, add apple juice and vanilla and let stand for a few minutes. Stir in flour that has been mixed with baking soda or baking powder. Fold in stiffly beaten egg white. Bake on nonstick griddle or skillet using 1/4 c. batter for each pancake.

title: quick saucy chicken stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium-high heat. Stir-fry veggies 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove. Add remaining oil to skillet.
Stir-fry chicken 4 minutes or until tender.
Return veggies.
Remove from heat.
Add combined remaining ingredients and mix well.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Slowly add sugar and vanilla to egg whites.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheets with foil.
Drop mixture by teaspoon on cookie sheets.
Place cookie sheets in oven and turn off heat.
Allow to remain in oven overnight.
Do not open oven door until morning.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: caribbean freeze
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sugar and cocoa; stir in water. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a boil; simmer 3 minutes.
Cool to room temperature; stir in concentrate and rum.
Chill.
Pour chilled mixture into 1-quart container.
Freeze.

title: corned beef noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into large pan.
Top with crumbs or chips.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables and soup, 1/2 cheese, sour cream, pepper and onions (1/2 of can).
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake covered 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake uncovered 5 minutes.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add cooked raisins, raisin juice and nuts.
Spoon by a teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan.
Mix together first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Combine milk, sour cream, oil, egg, chilies, cheese and corn.
Stir into dry ingredients until barely moistened.
Spoon into prepared pan and bake 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken chili
directions: In 8-quart saucepot, cook cut-up chicken in water until done, approximately 40 minutes, stirring several times.
Transfer chickens to a bowl to cool.
Skim fat off broth and discard. Reserve 3 cups broth.
(Cool and freeze leftover broth for soup or other recipes.)

title: porcupine balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, using only 1/2 of a can of tomato sauce together.
Make into balls about the size of an orange.
Place the balls in a Pyrex dish and pour the remaining tomato sauce over the balls.
Cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coleslaw mold
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water and vinegar.
Stir in mayonnaise, sour cream, mustard and onion, blending thoroughly.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in cabbage, pimiento and parsley.
Pour into 4-cup mold or serving bowl. Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill.

title: pizzelle
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs (room temperature) for at least 5 minutes, then add sugar.
Beat until thick and lemon-colored.
In a small bowl, mix oil, anise and Crisco.
Then add it to the egg mixture.
Using a fork, slowly add flour.
Do not beat.
Heat iron.
When iron is hot, put a little oil on a teaspoon (to prevent sticking) and dip into mixture.
Drop walnut size batter into center of hot iron.
Be careful iron does not get too hot. Cook for about 45 seconds to 1 minute on each side or until light golden brown.
After cooled, store in coffee cans.
Freezes well. Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: ghost cookies
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave or in a double boiler.
Dip the cookie two thirds of the way into the bark and drain excess chocolate.
Place on waxed paper and lightly place small chocolate chips for eyes.
Let almond bark harden and you have ghosts!

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add the cream cheese and beat with mixer until it melts.
Add cold water and refrigerate until it starts to set.
Stir in the fruit, marshmallows and whipped topping.
Let set until firm.

title: crazy cake
directions: Don't stir.
Put together in order and smooth in a 9 x 13-inch pan or cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: classic baked pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare pasta as package directs.
In a large bowl, combine pasta, sauce, beef, mushrooms and 2 cups cheese.
Turn into 13 x 9-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake for 45 minutes, covered with foil.
Uncover pan and top with remaining 2 cups of cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes uncovered.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Crush the Oreo cookies.
Mix together with 1 stick butter, melted.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with the ice cream. Press the peanuts into the top of the ice cream.
Freeze.
Boil together for 8 minutes the milk, 1 stick butter, chocolate chips and powdered sugar. Cool and spread over ice cream.
Keep frozen.

title: electric skillet fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in electric skillet at 280°. Bring to a boil, then turn heat down but keep boiling for 6 minutes, stirring constantly. Turn skillet off and add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until well blended. Pour into pan and chill, if necessary.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper, carrot and celery.
Add to bread cubes, ham and 1/2 cheese; mix well.
Pour into greased oblong casserole pan.
Beat egg and milk; pour over bread.
Mix.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add rest of cheese. Continue until cheese is melted.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburg, onion, garlic salt and taco seasoning.
Drain. Stir in tomato paste, water, oregano and chili seasoning.
In casserole, layer alternately beans, meat mixture and chips, ending with chips on top.
Bake at 350° covered for 45 minutes, then 10 minutes uncovered.
Add toppings (cheese, tomatoes and lettuce).

title: dutch butter cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy; add egg and beat well. Gradually stir in flour, blend well.
(Dough will be sticky.) Divide in half.
Place each half in well greased 8-inch square pan.
With floured hands, press dough into pans.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until browned.
Remove; cut into 2-inch squares while warm.
Remove and cool.

title: pink cloud pie
directions: Bring pineapple to boil.
Add gelatin and let cool.
Add cottage cheese and whipped topping.
Refrigerate until set or about 1 hour then serve.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven.
Bake until center is firm.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add the 1/4 cup of water.
Add the fruits.
Pour 1/2 gelatin mixture in bowl or mold.
Allow to gel (refrigerate).
Spread sour cream over jelled mixture.
Gently pour remainder of jello mixture over sour cream and leave set.

title: chicken cacciatore northern style
directions: Heat olive oil in large frying pan.
Saute chicken over medium heat, turning occasionally, for approximately 20 minutes.
While chicken browns, add onion, garlic and shallots to pan.
After 20 minutes or so, add wine, vinegar, salt, pepper and basil to mixture.
Cover tightly and allow to simmer for another 30 minutes.
Serve with pasta, rice or vegetables.
Serves 4.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup warm water.
Combine soup, cream cheese and gelatin in saucepan.
Heat until smooth.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Put in mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: coconut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat eggs and extract, then sour cream.
Add coconut.
Stir together the flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Beat into batter.

Divide between 2 lightly greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until bread tests clean when a toothpick inserted in the center comes out without any clinging batter or wet crumbs.

title: holiday cider
directions: Slice orange into 6 wedges; stud wedges with cloves.
Set aside.
Combine cider and candies in a Dutch oven over medium heat. Cook until candies are dissolved and mixture is thoroughly heated. Pour cider mixture into heatproof punch bowl.
Add clove-studded orange wedges and cinnamon sticks.
Serve hot.
(Works well in crock-pot to keep hot.)

title: beef stew
directions: Cube stew meat in 1 1/2 inch cubes; flour and brown. Add tomatoes, bay leaf, salt and pepper. Simmer gently for 30 minutes; add potatoes, carrots, onions, and another c. of tomatoes or water; cover and cook slowly until vegetables are tender. If desired, gravy may be thickened with a little flour.

title: pumpkin fluff dip
directions: Mix together pudding, pumpkin and pumpkin spice.
Fold in thawed cool whip.
Chill until serving.
You can dip graham cracker sticks into this or spread onto pumpkin cake.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a slow oven at 300° to 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until set.

title: celebrated chicken
directions: Saute onion in butter until onions are clear; set aside.
Mix juice of 3 lemons with garlic powder, oregano, salt and pepper. Dip chicken in mixture and rub in.
Place chicken in baking dish; cover with remaining lemon mixture and onion mixture.
Seal dish with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut
directions: You will need clean canning jars with lids.

title: chicken soup prinanier
directions: Combine celery, tomatoes, carrots, onion and basil in a medium saucepan and cook about 5 minutes.
Add broth and simmer until vegetables are tender. Season to taste.
Makes 4 servings. Contains about 40 calories per serving.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and beat.
Alternate dry ingredients with milk (put soda in sour milk).
Add rhubarb and vanilla.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup brown or white sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and nuts.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and bananas.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine dry ingredients; stir gently, alternating with liquid, into the creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in loaf pan.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs, add milk, water, sugar and flour.
Put corn into greased casserole pan.
Pour liquid mixture over, top with seasoned salt and bake at 350 F for 1 hour.

title: citrus salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple and juice.
Blend in the rest of the ingredients.
Can be served in bowl, but looks great in 9 x 12 pan with cherries as a garnish.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Mix 1 cup graham cracker crumbs with melted butter and line an 8-inch pan.
Combine egg yolks, sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind. Cook over very low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Chill and fold in whipped cream.
Beat egg whites until they stand in peaks and fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into lined pan and sprinkle with remaining graham cracker crumbs.
Wrap in moisture vapor-proof wrapping paper and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: fried turkey
directions: Slice turkey breast or use turkey cutlets already sliced. Roll in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Fry in butter, adding butter often to keep from burning.
Cook slowly until cooked fully.

title: peach pie
directions: Sprinkle peaches with lemon juice and sugar. Let stand 1 hour. Drain; reserve syrup. Measure 1 cup syrup (add water if necessary). Add to cornstarch and blend. Stir over low heat until thick. Remove from heat. Add oleo, salt and extract. Mix with peaches. Pour into pie shell. Chill.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat.
Add Ragu sauce and simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.
Cook noodles until tender and drain. Place noodles on foil to dry.
Place one layer of noodles in a large casserole dish.
Then add layer of hamburger meat.
Add layer of Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese; then repeat these steps again.
Place in oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients. Stir
dry
ingredients into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into coffee cans or into loaf pans.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: marinated salad
directions: Mix lemon juice, onion, chestnuts, mushrooms and cauliflower, using only 1/2 of broccoli stems.

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan.
Mix together all ingredients. Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix the ingredients in the order listed.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon; add onion and celery (chopped).
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir in flour.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Add clams and juice.
Season to taste.
Bring chowder to a boil again.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add potatoes and simmer again for 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix in a blender butter, honey, eggs, vanilla and carrots (cut up).
Process at medium speed until carrots are in fine pieces.
In a bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Add carrot mixture to dry ingredients and stir until combined.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Moisten fruit with mayonnaise.
Fold in whipped cream. Freeze in refrigerator tray for 3 hours. Remove by running a knife around the inside. Serve on slices of lettuce and garnish with 1 teaspoon mayonnaise and a cherry.

title: nine layer salad
directions: *May use low-fat varieties for low-fat and low-cholesterol diet.

title: old-fashioned vinegar pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs,
vinegar,	flour or cornstarch and water in double boiler.
Cook
until
thickened
and
smooth, stirring occasionally.
Just
before
removing from heat, stir in butter and lemon extract.	Pour
into
baked pie shell.
If desired, pie may be topped with whipped topping.

title: kraut and wieners
directions: Cut wieners in 1/2-inch pieces and brown in a little oil.
Add kraut, cook a little longer or you may boil wieners and add to kraut without fat.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk together in a saucepan.
Boil for 1 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet or wax paper.
Cool until firm.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and bell pepper together.
Place mixture in 1-quart casserole.
Mix 1/2 can of water with soup.
Pour over beef mixture.
Place Tater Tots on top and press down.
Sprinkle with grated cheese, if desired.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of 10 x 14-inch casserole dish.
Pour Veg-All over chicken; do not stir.
Mix broth with celery soup and pour over top of vegetables.
Mix milk, flour and butter; pour over top of dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Fry and crumble sausage.
Tear bread into little pieces.
Mix together.
Add cheese.
Put mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Beat together 6 eggs, 2 cups milk, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon dry mustard.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate mint patties
directions: Sift together confectioners sugar and cocoa.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine, corn syrup and extract until well blended.
Gradually beat in 1 to 2 cups of the cocoa mixture until well blended and smooth.
With wooden spoon, stir in remaining cocoa mixture.
With hand, knead until mixture is well blended and smooth.

title: valerie's barbecued pig's feet
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pot of water, enough to completely cover the trotters.
Boil until feet are soft, just about all day.
When done, arrange feet in shallow baking dish, using slotted spoon to avoid excess liquid.
Coat feet liberally with your favorite barbecue sauce; one that is spicy and full of smoke flavor.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, until edges of brown begin to show, usually about 1 hour.

title: slim and trim mayonnaise
directions: Put all ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir well and then add buttermilk slowly.
Keeps good in refrigerator or may use low-calorie dressing.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla alternately with dry ingredients.
Roll thin and cut with cookie cutters.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli according to package directions.
Put back in pan.
Cut up cheese and add to broccoli.
Heat until cheese melts; stir often.
In another pan, melt margarine; add crackers and mix well.
In baking dish, alternate layers of broccoli, then cracker mix.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
You can prepare ahead, refrigerate, then heat for 15 minutes.

title: boiled rabbit dinner
directions: Place rabbit in kettle with lightly salted water to cover and cook until just tender.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Set aside until cool in a separate bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add cooled ingredients from 1st bowl.
Mix and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: finger chicken
directions: Mix together and boil until thickened, stirring constantly. Pour over miniature chicken legs or wrap.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes and then turn over and bake another 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: cranberry-pineapple salad
directions: Mix jello, water and cranberry sauce well; add pineapple. Mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and chill overnight.
Ground nutmeats may be added if desired.

title: quick and easy zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients at low speed.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: happiness is homemade
directions: Mix well and serve daily!!!

title: munner's lollipops
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook without stirring until it forms a hard crackle in water.
Add flavoring and color.
Pour into well oiled ice tray.
Press in stick and allow to cool.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: marshmallow delight
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Stir occasionally so it doesn't scorch.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Roll graham crackers to crumbs.
Put 1/2 of crumbs on bottom of pan.
Reserve other 1/2 for top.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Layer vanilla wafers.
Layer bananas, sliced from top to bottom or long way.
Alternate up to 5 or 6 layers, ending with wafers. Whip the cream and ice.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: pam's breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add flour, baking powder and salt. Mix well.
Add the remaining ingredients. Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: corn & sausage casserole
directions: Crumble Sausage and brown until done.
Drain well.
Beat eggs. Mix sausage, corn, sugar, flour, milk, and dash of pepper. Sprinkle crushed Ritz and butter on top.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix together.
Pour in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Add bread crumbs or graham cracker crumbs.
Serve warm.

title: cheddar apple bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk and margarine and add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: wassail(waasul)
directions: Boil and simmer.
For full gallon, triple measurements.
All ingredients can be added to or subtracted from per taste.

title: tropical orange cooler
directions: Combine juice concentrate, water, dry milk powder and coconut flavoring in container of an electric blender; top with cover and process 30 seconds.

title: jello cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed on box.
Just before taking out of oven, boil 2 cups of water.
While water is boiling, punch holes all through the cake.
It may tear up, but the more holes the better the jello will be distributed.
Dissolve jello in the boiling water and, while cake and jello are still hot, pour all of the jello evenly over cake.
Put cake in refrigerator until jello is completely jelled, 5 or 6 hours.
Spread Cool Whip over cake. Add sprinkles.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening; add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix soda in buttermilk and add alternately with flour to sugar mixture.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans. Pour in 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix chicken, celery, onion, Miracle Whip, soup and salt together; put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole or pan.
Top with potato chips and cheese.
Sprinkle almonds on top. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs, garlic, salt, pepper and oregano.
Slice
eggplant and dip in egg mixture, then in other mixture.
Fry until golden brown.
Place in baking dish and cover with sauce and Mozzarella cheese.

title: baked yams with amaretti topping
directions: Bake yams in a 400° oven for 45 minutes or until tender. Scoop out the flesh and mash it with brown sugar, Amaretto liqueur, 2 tablespoons butter and salt.
Spread the yams mixture in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pulverize the Amaretti cookies between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Blend in the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter.
Sprinkle the cookie crumbs on the yams. Preheat the oven to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add oats, coconut and gumdrops.
Roll into small balls and put onto greased cookie sheet.
Press flat with fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small balls and flatten.
Cook on ungreased pan at 300 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: chicken flavored rice
directions: In medium saucepan, bring the chicken broth to a boil.
Add rice.
Cover.
Reduce heat to very low and simmer for approximately 18 to 20 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.
Add salt and pepper.

title: cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, then add milk; beat.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; beat together.
Pour into graham cracker crust; chill. Spoon pie filling over pie.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Trim root ends and tough outer leaves from leeks; slit each leek lengthwise, rinse between layers, then thinly slice.
In a 6-quart kettle over medium heat, cook leeks and garlic in oil, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Add stock, beans, anything liquid, vegetables, basil, oregano and rosemary; bring to simmering.
Reduce heat; cover and cook for 30 minutes.
Stir in tomato paste and macaroni, continue simmering for 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Add cabbage and cook, covered, just until it wilts (about 5 minutes).
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Pass parrue sauce at the table.
Makes eight 2-cup servings.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl except marshmallows and milk. Mix together ingredients.
Put marshmallows and milk in pot and melt at low temperature.
When melted, pour over mixture and mix well.
Place in any kind of dish you prefer.
Top it off with pecan halves.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Trim off loose pieces of breast.
Put in processor with cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Blend together.
Put on breast and fold over.
Prepare bread crumbs.
Beat egg in bowl.
Dip breast in crumbs and then dip in the egg (repeat).
Fry in butter and oil. Brown slightly.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Smash vanilla wafers with rolling pin.
Melt 1/4 pound margarine.
Mix well together; spread in a 13 x 9-inch casserole. Refrigerate for 20 minutes.
Mix the cream cheese and 1/4 pound margarine; spread on wafers.
Spread crushed pineapple, banana slices and strawberry slices.
Add Cool Whip on top.
Top with crushed walnuts or pecans.

title: mississippi mud brownies
directions: Grease 13 x 9 pan. Preheat oven to 350°. Mix together sugar, eggs, flour, chopped nuts, oil, 6 tablespoons cocoa, salt and vanilla. Bake 30 minutes. Just before cake is done, mix frosting. If you do this too early, it will get thick and hard to frost.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions until just tender.
Drain in a colander and rinse under cold running water; drain well.
Drop green beans into a large pot of rapidly boiling water.
When water returns to a full boil, cook for 2 to 3 minutes, or until beans are crisp-tender.
Drain and rinse under cold running water; drain well.
Gently toss tortellini with beans, tomatoes and just enough Creamy Vinaigrette to moisten, about 1/2 cup.

title: dr. tansil's cookies(velvet stars)
directions: Mix oleo and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and dry ingredients. Roll in small balls and bake about 10 minutes at 350°.
Yield: About 8 dozen.

title: black devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa and soda together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chili con carne
directions: Saute beef in shortening; add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: egg-shrimp divine
directions: Mix cream cheese with mayonnaise and curry powder; beat until smooth.
Press into a shallow soup bowl.
Mix thoroughly the shrimp, egg, onions and celery.
Press shrimp mixture into cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Chill to blend flavors.
Serve with crackers.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Separate 5 eggs and beat first 5 egg whites until stiff gradually with 1 cup of the sugar.
Cream Crisco and 2 cups sugar until light and fluffy.
Add all flavorings and 1 whole egg and beat well.
Add the 5 egg yolks and beat well.
Sift both kinds of flour and salt together.
Add soda to sour cream and stir well. Using a medium mixing speed, add flour and sour cream alternately to the creamed mixture.
Slowly blend egg whites and pour into tube pan that has been greased and dusted with flour.
Place in cold oven and set temperature to 325°.
Bake 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Do not open oven during baking time.

title: winter white chili
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, melt butter or margarine; add ground turkey.
Cook until brown.
Add chopped onion, minced garlic, ground cumin, basil leaves, oregano, salt, pepper, sage and thyme, stirring frequently.
Add chicken broth and beans.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until beans are tender.
Serves 6.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together (except chips).
Put in a casserole dish and top with chips.
Cover and bake in oven for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake for an additional 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pound cake and a half
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add salt and baking powder to flour.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Grease and flour tube pan. Add strip of foil to top.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
This cake rises about 1 inch above pan.

title: o'charley's caramel pie
directions: Place unopened can of condensed milk into pan of water making sure water covers can at all time.
Bring to boil.
Continue to boil slowly for 4 hours.
Remove can from water, when cooled enough to handle, open and spoon the caramelized milk into the crust.
Top with whip cream and mini chocolate chips.
If using condensed milk that has been boiled ahead, set can of milk in warm water before pouring into crust.

title: rice and green chili casserole
directions: Cook rice until just tender.
Add butter, salt and pepper. Mix chopped green chilies and sour cream in separate container. Butter casserole, and alternate layers of well seasoned rice, sour cream and chilies and cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with sour cream.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter and sharp cheese (you can grate sharp cheese on top if you like). Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain well.
Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Simmer, covered, at least 2 hours or all day in crock-pot.
Serves 10.
Freezes well.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: In a saucepan, combine gelatin and cold water; let stand 5 minutes to soften.
Heat and stir over low heat just until gelatin dissolves.
Remove from heat; add sugar.
Stir until dissolved. Stir in undrained strawberries.
Chill until partially thickened. Fold in whipped topping.
Place cake cubes in a mixing bowl; pour strawberry mixture over cake and mix gently.
Pour into an ungreased 8-inch square baking dish.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with fresh strawberries and mint if desired.
Yields 9 servings.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and heat until very warm. Combine this warm liquid gradually with 2 cups flour and remaining ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour to make enough dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and divide into 2 loaves or 24 rolls.
Let rise again until doubled.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and sounds hollow to tap.
Brush the warm loaves with honey and butter mixture.

title: ants on a log
directions: Cut celery into pieces and spread with peanut butter.
Top with raisins, coconut or grated carrots.
(Celery is difficult for younger children to chew.)

title: pistachio cream cheese dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and spread in 9 x 13 greased pan. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°. Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar, add one cool whip and spread on top of the crust.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine.
Add both sugars and cream until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and baking powder (sifted together) alternately with milk.
Add vanilla. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Melt shortening and saute potatoes, parsley, onion, one bay leaf, salt and pepper over medium heat.
Then cook covered 15 to 20 minutes over low heat.
Add chicken stock and cook 15 minutes. Mix half and half with flour and stir into soup.
Keep stirring so no lumps form.
Simmer soup for at least 30 minutes.
Add grated carrots and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown meat (drain), add cheese, stirring until melted.
Mix together well.
Put on rye bread and freeze on cookie sheets. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix together meat, eggs and salt.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls and roll in raw rice to coat.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix together the tomato paste and water; pour over meatballs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours, or until rice is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: bacon and potato soup
directions: Melt butter (margarine).
Add sliced onion (do not brown). Cook gently.
Add potatoes and white pepper.
Pour milk and broth over potatoes.
Cover and cook gently for 20 to 25 minutes, or until potatoes are very tender.

title: sopos
directions: Fry the beans until they are dry (no liquid).
Set aside.
Fry the corn tortillas flat until they are hard.
Set aside.
Take flat fried tortilla, put or spread beans on first.
Next, add white cheese, tomato and lettuce.
Squeeze lemon on top.
Add salt to taste.
This is now ready to eat.
You can serve it with Mexican rice and top it with Pico de Gallo.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Line pie plate with cookies.
Soften ice cream.
On top of cookies, layer ice cream, then crushed candy bars.
Repeat layers. Freeze.
Dribble caramel sauce on sliced pie when ready to serve.
Yummy!
Yields one pie.

title: easy cream cheese fudge
directions: Melt chips and margarine.
Add softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Place in a well-buttered pan and refrigerate until set.
Store in refrigerator.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix and pour in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and flour.
Melt butter and blend with egg mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until tested done.

title: sausage party balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or 1/4 hour, then freeze and cook later.
Serve hot with toothpicks in center.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook like fudge until soft ball forms in cold water (235°). Cool.
Add last two ingredients and beat until it changes color. Pour into buttered pan.

title: chicken stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops of green peppers; remove seeds and membrane.
Saute onion in small amount of tomato liquid; add tomatoes, rice, Tabasco, pepper, chicken and 1/2 of the cheese.
Stand peppers upright in an 8-inch square baking dish; stuff with tomato-rice filling.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: party vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook vegetables until tender-crisp; drain.
Drain corn.
Gently mix and place in greased casserole. Mix soup, milk (or half and half) and seasonings.
Pour over vegetables; stir gently.
If desired, sprinkle top with grated cheese (Cheddar, Swiss or Parmesan) and paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: creamy style jigglers
directions: Pour gelatin in a bowl.
Add boiling water.
Stir with a rubber scraper until gelatin is completely dissolved, approximately 2 minutes.
Cool to room temperature, approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken, reserving broth in Dutch oven; discard vegetables and bay leaf.
Let chicken cool; skin, bone and cut into bite-size pieces.

title: mole poblano
directions: Drain broth off chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer gently 10 minutes.
Remove chicken to serving platter; keep warm.
Cook and stir sauce until slightly thickened, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Spoon over chicken.
Can double recipe but do not double the cocoa.
Serve with Spanish rice.

title: baked liver
directions: Brown liver on both sides in olive oil using a skillet.
Saute chopped up celery and onions; set aside.
Use a Dutch oven and place liver pieces in bottom.
Pour in celery and onions.
Then top with stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Bake in oven at 375° for 1 hour.
Delicious served over white rice.
(Do not cook liver on top of stove until done.
Just brown it lightly on both sides. It cooks done in the oven.)

title: broiled chicken with cheddar sauce
directions: Broil chicken inches from heat, for 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Remove chicken and place onto plate, cover and set aside.
In saucepan, over high heat, bring broth to boil. Add potatoes and pepper.
Bring to boil, cover and reduce to low heat.
Let simmer until potatoes are tender.
This takes around 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In skillet over medium-high heat, warm the oil until hot.
Add onion and cook until slightly softened, stirring constantly.
This takes 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the flour and continue to cook until flour is no longer visible.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Remove potatoes from broth and place in food processor or blender.
Measure out 1/2 cup of the broth and add to blender along with the onion mixture.
Blend until smooth.
Add Cheddar and any chicken juices that are on the plate; mix well.
Place sauce onto the chicken breast and serve.

title: cold weather chili
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven or a heavy large saucepan.
Sprinkle the meat with flour.
Brown in oil.
Add a little extra oil to the browned meat, if needed.
Stir in onion, green pepper and garlic. Cook until soft.
Stir in the beef broth, oregano, cumin, chili powder and salt.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes.
Stir in tomato sauce and chocolate. Simmer, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes until thickened.
Serve hot.

title: pink peanut patties
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, water and peanuts.
Cook until it forms a soft ball.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Beat until it begins to get stiff, then drop on waxed paper.

title: fred's favorite cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix above ingredients thoroughly. Heat 1 tablespoon bacon grease in heavy black skillet.
Pour 1/2 of the heated bacon grease into bread mixture, leaving remaining grease in skillet.
Sprinkle hot skillet with a little corn meal. Pour batter into skillet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
(I brush the top with butter during the last 10 minutes of cooking time and, if necessary, put under the broiler until top is golden brown.)
Let cool for 5 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: working girls chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and small amount of garlic powder.
Dilute soup with milk.
Place chicken in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with soup.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: toffee bars
directions: Melt butter, add sugar and boil 2 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour sugar mixture over saltines that have been placed on foil-lined jelly roll pan.
Do not stack saltines, place them side by side.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not brown.
Remove from oven. Pour morsels over, they will melt.
Spread evenly.
Cool.
Crack into bite size pieces.

title: meringue tart shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt and cream of tartar.
Gradually add sugar while continuing to beat egg whites, until stiff peaks form.
Beat in extract and food coloring.
Put brown paper on large cookie sheets.
Drop meringue by very small teaspoons, shaping for a tart shell on the brown prepared cookie sheets.
(They will spread.)
Place pans in preheated 350° oven.
Do not put on lowest rack.
Turn oven off immediately and let pans remain in closed oven overnight.
This recipe may be made smaller by dividing the ingredients in half.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Combine ingredients and set aside.
Prepare Marinade.

title: finger lickin' chicken
directions: Marinate chicken pieces in the mixture made by combining catsup, soy sauce, honey and lemon juice.
Marinate at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: meal in a frypan
directions: Brown beef in skillet. Stir in all other ingredients except corn.
Mix well and heat thoroughly, about 20 to 30 minutes. Stir occasionally. Cover while cooking. Add corn and heat 5 more minutes.

title: wine-sauced shoulder chops
directions: For sauce:
Cook onion, pimiento, herbs and pepper in hot oil until onion is tender.
Combine cornstarch, Worcestershire and 1/3 cup cold water.
Stir into onion mixture.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add wine.
Keep sauce warm.

title: country pork chops
directions: Spread sauerkraut over the bottom of a Dutch oven.
Sprinkle seeds on top.
Salt and pepper the meat to taste and lay on top of the kraut.
Put on cover and bake at 325° at least 3 1/2 hours (remove the cover the last 1/2 hour).
Serve with cold applesauce and jalapeno corn bread

title: hot fruit dish
directions: Drain
juice
from
fruit.
Make
a
sauce
of 1 cup of juice, 1/2
cup
sugar,
2 tablespoons of flour and 1/2 or 2/3 stick
of margarine.
Cook
until
thickened.
Place layer of pineapple, layer of pears, layer of peaches and layer of apple rings.
Pour sauce over the fruit.
Refrigerate overnight and then heat until hot.

title: curried kidney beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and saute onions, peppers, apples and curry powder until tender.
Place tomatoes in a colander and squeeze until all liquid is removed (reserve liquid for other uses).
Combine drained tomatoes with onion mixture, kidney beans, brown sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper in a casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.
Especially good with baked ham.
Serves 12.

title: african chow mein
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter and brown hamburg separately.
Put everything together in 13 x 9-inch pan or 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Last 3 minutes, put onion rings on top.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Can be rolled into powdered sugar, if preferred.

title: whole kernel corn bread
directions: Coat a 9-inch cast-iron skillet with 1/2 teaspoon oil.
Place skillet in a 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Combine remaining 3 tablespoons oil and remaining ingredients in a bowl, stirring well.
Pour into skillet.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cut corn bread into wedges.
Yields 12 servings.

title: steak and beans
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in Mazola oil.
Brown the meat after cutting into cubes.
Pour in red wine after seasoning.
Let meat stew until tender.
Open cans of goya red kidney beans and pour into sauteed meat, onions and peppers.
Serve over big platter of yellow rice.

title: hearty taco soup
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven with green pepper and onion.
Add to beef the tomatoes, beans, corn, chili powder, cumin, garlic powder and cayenne pepper.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add seasonings to taste.
Put taco chips in each bowl.
Add soup and top with grated cheese.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Roll 4 biscuits to thin circles.
Layer bottom of 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Pour peaches in.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over top of peaches.
Dot with butter.
Roll 4 more biscuits to thin circles.
Cover peaches.
Sprinkle more cinnamon, sugar and butter on top crust.
Place in preheated oven at 375° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown and crusty.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time. Add flour alternately with buttermilk (and dissolved soda). Roll dates, candy, pecans and coconut in flour and add to butter mixture. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan in 250° oven for 2 1/2 hours. Test to see if done.

title: salad louise (spinach salad)
directions: Mix ingredients and add Sweet-Sour Dressing.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Beat eggs before putting them in.
Put meal in last.
Bake like corn bread.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done; drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Combine cheese and mushroom soup.
Mix together.
Pour over broccoli.
Crush croutons mixed with butter.
Pour over all. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tuscan soup
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, saute onion and carrot in oil until vegetables are tender.
Add broth, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in beans and pasta; return to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until pasta is cooked, stirring occasionally.
Add spinach and heat through.
Serves 4.

title: guest stew
directions: Mix salad dressing according to package directions.
Combine 1/4 cup of the salad dressing with the soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Marinate beef in the sauce for 3 hours.
Coat beef lightly with flour and brown in heated salad oil in heavy skillet. Transfer meat to a Dutch oven and top with carrots, onion and mushrooms.
Add enough water to just cover the meat and vegetables. Cover Dutch oven and bake in preheated 300° oven for 3 hours or until beef is tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
May serve with hot cooked rice or noodles if you wish.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: blueberry banana pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Cover bottoms of the pie crusts with the sliced bananas. Cream the cream cheese with 2 tablespoons lemon juice. Slowly add the powdered sugar until smooth. Fold in the Cool Whip and cover bananas in pie crusts.
Chill for 1 hour.
Add 2 tablespoons lemon juice to the pie filling.
Spread on the top of the pies and chill.

title: tequilaberry's salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, Parmesan cheese and sugar an hour or so ahead so flavors blend.
Fry bacon and break up; set aside. Break up lettuce and cauliflower.
Just before serving, mix with dressing and add bacon.

title: healthy oatmeal cookies(low-fat cookies)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until just done.

title: bubblies
directions: Mix frozen lemonade according to directions in a large container.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Chill before serving.

title: 24 hour ambrosia salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Put in refrigerator for 24 hours to blend together.

title: gourmet chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, celery, rice, soup, mayonnaise, onion, water chestnuts, mushrooms and lemon juice; stir.
Place in a glass 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover with Corn Flake crumbs.
Pour melted butter over the top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy beef goulash
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Put dry egg noodles on meat.
Combine soup mix, water and tomato sauce.
Pour over egg noodles. Cover and cook on medium for 30 minutes.

title: "lotsa" sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until thick.
I
mix and cook it in crock-pot.
Makes approximately 30 sandwiches.
Can freeze also.

title: rice with black beans
directions: Cook and stir onion in hot oil until tender, but not browned. Add tomatoes, beans, oregano and garlic powder.
Bring to boil. Stir in rice.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 9 servings.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cool until firm.

title: minted mocha mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, use 3 heaping spoons in mug of hot water.
Contains 30 calories per tablespoon.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Bring peas to a boil.
Let sit.
Fry bacon real crisp.
Layer the ingredients.
Toss with the mayonnaise and sugar dressing. Better to let set overnight.
May put dressing on top of salad and toss later.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, cocoa and 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil; stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
In large bowl, sift together flour and sugar; stir in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla. Add cocoa mixture; mix until blended.
Pour into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Immediately pour frosting over brownies.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Layer raw meat in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle onion mix on meat, then the two cans of soup (undiluted) on top of that.
Then add the Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour (the Tater Tots will be golden brown when ready).

title: simply italian
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic, basil, mushrooms and tomatoes; cook 5 minutes.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper.
Cook approximately 10 minutes; stir often until tender, but crisp.
Pour over cooked pasta; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Mix sugar and chocolate.
Add milk and water.
Cook slow.
Mix flour in water.
Add to syrup to thicken.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, spices and baking powder.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spread into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Top with 1 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel.
Roll and cool.
Unroll.
Spread filling over roll and roll again.
Chill and serve.
Enjoy!

title: pina colada wedges
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar and rum until smooth.
Fold in 2 cups of Cool Whip, pineapple and 2 cups of coconut.
Spread in 8-inch layer pan lined with plastic wrap.
Invert pan onto serving plate.
Remove pan and plastic wrap.
Spread with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Freeze until firm, about 2 hours. Cut.
Garnish with pineapple and cherries.

title: venison roast
directions: Chill meat that has been cleaned and cubed. Add 1/2 teaspoon salt to each quart jar. Pack meat in jar tight. Do not add liquid. Pressure cook 90 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: potato pancakes(preparation time: 30 minutes.  serves 6.)
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water.
When cooked, pass potatoes through a food mill or sieve with fine holes.
Place puree in electric mixer.
Add cornstarch and mix.
Slowly incorporate eggs and egg whites, then heavy cream.
Season to taste.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Coarsely break taco shells.
In a 2-quart bowl, mix beef and onion.
Cover bowl with waxed paper.
Cook at High for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring and breaking up meat into small pieces every 2 minutes.
Tilt bowl, skim and discard excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and chili powder.
Cover.
Cook at High for 4 minutes or until meat mixture thickens, stirring after 2 minutes. Stir in undrained green chilies and shredded cheese.

title: satin pie for angels
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick: egg yolks, sugar, milk and salt.
Add gelatin which has been dissolved in cold water.
Cool. Add vanilla, stiffly beaten egg whites and whipped cream.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds and chill until ready to serve.
Makes a light dessert.

title: strawberry-rhubarb ice cream pie
directions: Spoon softened ice cream into crust.
Freeze.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan over medium heat, cook rhubarb and sugar, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves and mixture boils.
Combine cornstarch and water; stir into saucepan.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Cool.
Fold in berries and chill.
Spread over ice cream.
Let stand 10 minutes at room temperature before cutting.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Using a 9 x 13-pinch pan which has been Pammed, put rice on bottom.
Cover with mixture of soups and milk, then chicken on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: lemon somethings
directions: Combine beaten egg with melted margarine.
Mix in cake mix and press into 13 x 9 inch pan.
Press nuts into crust.
Mix cream cheese, 2 beaten eggs and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of crust. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes in 8 or 9-inch pan.
Serve warm with milk.
Freezes well. Makes 8 muffins or 8-inch square pan.

title: summer sausage 1
directions: Mix thoroughly and shape into 3 rolls. Chill 24 hours. Bake on rack in preheated 250° oven for approximately 3 1/2 hours.

title: grilled sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in a steamer basket; place over boiling water, cover and steam 5 to 7 minutes.
Combine soy sauce and next 4 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Add sweet potatoes and toss gently.
Drain sweet potatoes, reserving soy sauce mixture.

title: pumpkin pie(kindergarten recipe)
directions: Pour cinnamon on apples.
Stir in pumpkin.
Pour all the stuff in a silver container.
Put it in the oven.
Cook for 5 minutes. Take it out and put a cherry on top and let it cool.

title: no-bake peach crisp
directions: Into a medium size saucepan measure 1/4 cup of the sugar.
Add cornstarch, salt and water.
Stir to dissolve, then cook over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add the remaining 3/4 cup of sugar and return to heat; cook until sugar is dissolved.
Add almond flavoring and fresh peaches.
Stir to mix thoroughly.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan or pie pan.
Top with cereal mixture, (or the fresh peach mixture can be poured directly into individual serving dishes and then topped with cereal mixture).
Serve with cream, whipped topping or ice cream.

title: orange delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and sugar together in a medium bowl.
Blend in the flour.
Mix well.
Add vanilla flavoring, crushed potato chips and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.

title: chocolate banana milk shakes
directions: Mash banana to a pulp.
Add chocolate milk and vanilla.
Shake well.
Or, slice banana into an electric blender, add remaining and blend until thick and creamy.

title: croutons or bread crumbs
directions: Cut bread into cubes.
Place in a single layer on paper towel in microwave.
Heat uncovered in microwave 1 to 2 minutes on High. Rearrange once.
Let stand 5 minutes.
During standing time, bread will completely dry.

title: sweet potato casserole 1
directions: Use tender fresh green beans. Prepare beans as needed.
Saute in a skillet with as little oil as possible and season to taste.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat together eggs, vanilla, sugar and vegetable oil.
Sift together baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry ingredients alternately with 2 cups grated or chopped raw zucchini (unpeeled) to egg mixture.
One cup of nuts may be added.
Bake in Bundt pan or two loaf pans for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: marie's tea cakes
directions: Mix all the ingredients in order as listed.
Drop on cookie sheet (spray with cooking spray) by spoon.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Combine peanut butter, oleo and confectioners sugar.
Roll into balls and stick on toothpicks.
Melt butterscotch or chocolate chips and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Dip balls into this and cool on waxed paper.

title: shaggy dogs(cookie)
directions: Boil slow together first
ingredients for 10 minutes or longer.
Stir in Rice Krispies, vanilla and nuts.
Cool and roll in coconut.

title: "homemade" fruit cake
directions: Butter pan and put wax paper in bottom.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook at 350° until firm.

title: mascarpone and honey sauce
directions: Let cheese sit in a bowl until slightly softened and ready for whipping.
With an electric beater, whip cheese and cream together.
While whipping, pour honey (to taste) into mixture. Whip only until mixture is thick but pourable, not stiff.
This is a dessert cream; great poured over fresh fruit.

title: green rice(broccoli casserole)
directions: *I use fresh broccoli flowers instead of frozen.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add chicken.
To serve, spoon over tortilla chips in bowls and top with grated Cheddar cheese and sour cream.

title: new england fish chowder
directions: Cook and stir onions in butter in a 2-quart saucepan until onion is tender (not browned).
Remove from heat.
Add haddock, potato, salt and pepper with enough water to cover.
Cover and cook until potato is tender and fish is flaky (about 15 minutes). Stir in milk and heat.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Peel and slice onions into thin rings.
Saute in margarine until done.
Pour 1/2 of onions in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with Parmesan cheese, then Ritz crackers.
Repeat layers and bake uncovered in 325° oven until golden brown, about 30 minutes. Yield:
7 servings.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: To cake
mix
add egg and oleo.
Press into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Stir in juice, vanilla and orange rind.
Blend dry ingredients; add to butter mixture.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: creole style pork chops
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with flour.
Brown slowly in fat.
Add tomatoes, chopped green pepper, chopped onion and salt.
Simmer 1 hour about 350° in oven.
Serve over cooked macaroni.

title: beef stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and dash of pepper.
Coat meat cubes in seasoned flour.
Brown in hot shortening in Dutch oven.
Add soup, 2 1/2 cups water, onion and basil.
Cover and bake in 375° oven about 1 hour.
Add potatoes, carrots and wine or water.
Cover and bake 1 hour longer or until tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate mousse pie(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Press on bottom and completely up sides of 10-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: yummy crab dip
directions: Blend all together (except the almonds); put in an ovenproof dish and sprinkle almonds on top. Bake 15 minutes at 375°. Serve with assorted crackers while hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl.
Use both hands to blend everything well.
Shape teaspoon size balls with hands.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze while raw.
After frozen, put in Ziploc bags.
Remove quantity you want and cook on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix the first three ingredients together.
Spoon out on to a greased cookie sheet.
Mash lightly with spoon and sprinkle on powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: potato bread
directions: In a bread bowl, pour 1 cup warm water.
Add 1 teaspoon honey. Do not stir.
Slowly sprinkle 1 tablespoon yeast into water, making sure each particle gets wet.
Again do not stir.
Wait 10 minutes, until the yeast is thick and foamy.
Add the following, stirring well between each addition:
mashed potatoes, 1 1/2 cups warm water, salt and 2 cups flour.
Then add oil.
Add remaining flour, 1 cup at a time, until you use up most of the 8 cups of flour. This dough will be too sticky to handle if you do not get enough flour into it at this time.
Knead dough on floured surface until smooth and elastic, 10 to 12 minutes.
Keep the surface lightly dusted with flour if the dough is too sticky to handle.
When dough is smooth and elastic, place into a greased bowl.
Turn it to grease the top.
Set in a warm, draft-free spot and allow it to rise until double in bulk, 1 1/2 hours.
Punch dough down.
Pull it away from the sides of the bowl.
Turn it out onto a lightly floured kneading surface.
Knead the dough to remove the large air bubbles, 1 minute.
Cut it in half and set it aside to rest for 5 to 10 minutes.
Shape the dough into loaves.
Set in a warm, draft-free spot and allow to rise until double in size.
Bake in 400° oven for 35 minutes.
Cool immediately on a wire rack.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add other ingredients and let simmer about 1 hour.

title: loose sausage casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in casserole or small roasting pan and cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, make a layer of vanilla wafer crumbs.
Cream margarine, powdered sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Spread mixture over crumbs.
Cover with sliced strawberries or can mix berries in creamed mixture.
Chill for several hours or overnight before serving.
Serve with a whipped topping or Cool Whip on top.

title: christmas punch
directions: Combine water, sugar and cinnamon in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Cut a large pineapple lengthwise and scoop out the flesh.
Cut it into cubes and add diced portions of other suitable fruits, as desired.
Pour over the fruit mixture a syrup of sugar, water and a little lemon juice.
Sprinkle with freshly grated coconut. Serve chilled.
Serves 6.

title: basic vanilla ice cream(no cooking)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until thick.
Add milk, cream, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Pour mixture into gallon freezer container.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: tuna noodle casserole(serves 4)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions. Meanwhile, combine tuna and mushroom soup with 1/8 teaspoon cinnamon (vary cinnamon to your taste). Then combine noodles with tuna and mix in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle with a dash of cinnamon and breadcrumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Place all ingredients in pan and cook until soft ball forms in water.
Beat until creamy and dull looking.
Add vanilla and spread.
If icing hardens too much, add a few drops of hot water and stir well.

title: cheese grits
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, heat water to boiling.
Stir grits, salt and pepper into boiling water.
Cook, stirring until thickened and bubbly.
Cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and butter.
Cook until thick, then add lemon juice.
Pour over peaches and bake.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 400° for 10 minutes and then at 375° until done.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken with cumin, then debone and blend chicken soup, sour cream, olives and chilies in a large bowl.
Divide into 2 bowls.
Add chicken and 1/2 of two cheeses into large bowl. Spread 1/2 cup of chicken mixture onto shells and roll.
Lay into baking pan; spread other 1/2 of mix on top.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and
mix well.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350°.
This makes
2 regular
loaves,
or
to 8 small loaves.
Bake in regular
loaf pans approximately 1 hour.
After baking, brush with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture.

title: a man's salad
directions: Have fun.
Wash and tear lettuce.
Drain.
Wash and prepare other vegetables as desired (sliced, diced or chopped).
Add lettuce together with vegetables, meats and eggs.
Top with cheese and croutons.
Serve with choices of salad dressings.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together. Cover your hands with flour and roll dough into walnut size balls.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes. Great fun for kids.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix.
Store dry.
Mix 2 tablespoons with 1 cup hot water to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
In a large bowl, mix the first 4 ingredients.
When mixed well, add the corn tortillas to the mixture.
Mix well.
Place mixture in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbling.

title: steak-vegetable pockets
directions: Slice beef thinly into bite size strips.
In wok, stir-fry broccoli, carrot, onion and green pepper in 1 tablespoon hot oil 7 minutes.
Add pea pods, mushrooms and tomatoes; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Combine 1/4 cup cold water and soy sauce.
Blend in cornstarch.
Add to wok.
Stir until bubbly.
Return vegetables to wok, heat through.
Spoon into pita bread; top with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Mix with soups and cook until good and hot.

title: super hamburgers
directions: Combine all
but oil, mixing well.
Shape into patties and brush with oil.
Broil 4 to 6 minutes on each side.

title: party cheese sandwich
directions: Mix well and spread on party rounds.

title: biscuits
directions: To feed:
Add 1 cup flour, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 cup milk; mix. Don't use same day it is fed.
To make biscuits, mix ingredients all together.
Add one cup starter and 1/4 cup oil; stir.
Knead a few times.
Feed every three days.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Slice carrots and boil until tender, about 20 min. and then mash. Preheat oven 350 °.
Melt butter in casserole in oven.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add dry mixture to mashed carrots and mix well.
Mix together milk and eggs.
Add liquid mixture and stir.
Pour into buttered casserole.
DO NOT STIR.
Bake 45 min. If you plan to freeze simply melt the butter in glass cup and mix it with the other ingredients before pouring in dish. Serves 6.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Mix pudding mix, sour cream and pineapple in bowl; stir and mix well.
Pour into graham cracker crust; top with Cool Whip. Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serves 6.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Season well as preferred.
Mix and pour into shell.

title: marinated chinese vegetable salad
directions: Marinate at least 24 hours in these ingredients:
1 cup sugar, dissolved in 1/2 cup dark vinegar; add 1/4 cup oil and 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.

title: irish bread
directions: Blend shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients with milk.
Will be a soft batter.
Add raisins.
Bake 1 hour in a round 2-quart Pyrex dish or cast-iron frying pan (grease pan) in a 350° oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil rice until done.
Add chicken, soup, lemon juice, butter, grated cheese, mayonnaise and chicken broth.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Add flavoring and coconut. Pour into Bundt or tube pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Defrost spinach and squeeze out water.
Mix ingredients and chill.
Use sourdough round bread as bowl; cut a square out of the middle and cut into chunks to use to dip.
Place spinach dip into bread bowl.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: apple-oatmeal treats
directions: First halve, core and chop the apples.
Put them in a steamer, sprinkle with cinnamon and steam until tender, usually about 10 minutes.
(If you don't have a steamer, try placing a strainer in a pot with about 2 inches of water and cover.)
Next, combine all the other ingredients.
By the time you're done, the apples will be tender and aromatic from the cinnamon. Put them into a blender and liquefy.
Combine all ingredients and plop the batter by teaspoonfuls onto a nonstick cookie sheet (or one sprayed with Baker's Joy).
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
This will make 2 to 3 dozen cookies, depending on how big you make them.

title: double chocolate cloud cookies(heart healthy)
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar. Add sugar and milk (beat until well mixed). Sift in cocoa. Fold in chocolate chips. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 300° oven (line cookie sheets with parchment or brown paper).

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together in food processor, strawberry puree, sugar, and bananas. Place in bowl. Blend together cream cheese, marshmallow cream. Pour mixture in same bowl. Stir and fold in cool whip. When mixed well, chill 1-1/2 hours before serving.

title: shrimp broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except broccoli; add cooked broccoli to mixture; put in a 9 x 11-inch container.
Top with 1 pound of cooled shrimp (peeled).
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy baked chicken breast
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine and stir well.
Spoon evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45-55 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits according to directions on box.
Melt margarine and cheese roll together in saucepan.
Beat eggs well and pour into a measuring cup.
Fill to make 1 cup with milk.
Pour the cheese mixture into the grits; then add the egg mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This can be made early and refrigerated until baking time.
If this is done, bake 50 minutes.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In 6-quart saucepot in hot oil, brown roast on all sides. Spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 45 minutes or until roast and vegetables are fork-tender.
Remove roast and vegetables.

title: clam cream cheese dip(appetizer)
directions: Mix all ingredients slowly in an electric mixer until thoroughly incorporated.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: dill onion vinaigrette
directions: Combine ingredients in a jar.
Cover; shake vigorously.
Chill to blend flavors.
Shake again before serving with mixed garden salad.
Makes 1 cup.

title: pudding icing
directions: Blend until stiff (3 to 8 minutes).

title: pepper steak
directions: Sprinkle steak with paprika and set aside.
Brown garlic in butter and add steak, onions and green peppers.
Cook until all vegetables are wilted.
Add tomatoes and broth.
Cover and simmer on low heat about 15 minutes.
Blend water with cornstarch and soy sauce; stir into steak.
Cook until thickened.
Serve over rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: fettucini with tomato and basil sauce
directions: Put garlic, oil, tomatoes, salt and pepper in a saucepan. Cook 5 minutes.
Add basil.
Cook 5 minutes more.
Cook fettucini as directed.
Drain and toss with sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: hershey's doubly chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir (in separate bowl) the flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add this mixture to the butter-sugar mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spoon-drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: toasted almond party spread
directions: Mix ingredients together (except almonds).
Spread in a 9-inch pie/quiche dish.
Bake for 15 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.
Spread almonds on top after baking.

title: no bake fruitcake bars
directions: Mix pudding, margarine and milk.
Cook on medium heat until it boils.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add crumbs, fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Empty into pan and pack firmly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, salt and soda. Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.

Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. You may flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with tines of fork. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate chip dessert
directions: Spread a thin layer of Cool Whip in an 8 x 11-inch Pyrex dish. Layer cookies over the Cool Whip.
Continue to layer until the dish is full, finishing with Cool Whip.
(Small chocolate chip cookies with holes in the middle work best.) This is much better when made the night before serving it.

title: peanut butter and banana bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugars, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine mashed bananas, milk, peanut butter, oil, vanilla and egg.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Stir in chocolate chips. Pour batter into two greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool thoroughly on a wire rack.
Frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight. Rinse and drain.
Combine with other ingredients and pour over vegetable mixture.
Seal in hot sterile jars.

title: fresh tomato sauce
directions: If using fresh tomatoes, core them; cut into coarse chunks and puree in a food processor until smooth.
Strain the fresh or canned tomatoes through a fine sieve to remove the seeds.
Set aside.
In a deep heavy pot, heat the olive oil.
Add the onion and saute until soft.
Add the garlic and saute until soft.
Add the fresh or canned tomatoes and stir to blend.
Add the wine, salt, pepper and basil and stir well.
Bring to a boil; lower the heat and simmer for 25 minutes.
The sauce is ready to use, or it can be refrigerated up to 1 week or frozen up to 3 months.
Makes about 9 cups.

title: wassail
directions: Stud 3 oranges with whole cloves.
Place in pan with enough water to cover bottom.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Meanwhile mix all other ingredients and bring to boil.
Float oranges in Wassail.

title: pretzel salad or dessert
directions: Mix and press in baking pan, approximately 13 x 9-inch. Bake 8 minutes at 400°. Cool.

title: cynde's great chocolate cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine ingredients, except chocolate chips and confectioners sugar.
Beat at medium speed for 10 minutes. Fold in chocolate chips and pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool for about 20 minutes and remove from pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when completely cool.

title: banana nut chiffon cake
directions: Sift
flour,
sugar,
baking
powder,
salt and walnuts until well
