blended.
Make
a
well
in
center; add oil, egg yolks, bananas and vanilla.
Beat with a wooden spoon until a smooth batter forms.
Beat egg whites, gradually adding cream of
tartar until
firm
peaks	form.
Gently fold whites into batter.	Turn into
ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for
minutes, or until a pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool cake in pan inverted on rack.
With a sharp knife gently
loosen
cake from
sides,
then bottom of pan.
Cover cake; let stand several hours for flavor to develop.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or drizzle with powdered sugar glaze.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (except onions) in greased casserole bowl.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle onions over top. Return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: lime bisque deluxe
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Cool and let stand until partially set.
Take evaporated milk chilled and whipped stiff. Add juice from lemon.
Mix well.
Add jello mixture and beat until well blended.
Pour into a 9x13 pan that is lined with a graham cracker crust.
Let chill several hours to set, spread with cool whip topping and sprinkle with a little green sugar for decoration. You can use graham cracker crumbs as decoration also.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet and cook onion until clear.
Add soup and cook for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add rice and corn, one at a time, mixing well.
Add Cheez Whiz last and mix well. Cook in oven in casserole dish uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle dry rice into the bottom of a well-greased baking dish.
In a large bowl, combine cans of soup, mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Shake the unopened envelope of onion soup mix to mix well.
Add 1/2 of the envelope to the soup mixture in the bowl. Stir well.
Pour mixture over the rice.
Place chicken breasts over the soup.
Pour the cup of water over the chicken breasts and sprinkle the other half of the dry onion soup mix over the chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook frozen broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Then mix with all other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creole porcupines
directions: Melt butter and stir into sugar; beat in eggs.
Add pecans, dates and 1 cup of the coconut.
Form into small balls and roll in the remaining 2 cups of coconut.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 300° until cookies just begin to brown lightly, about 25 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen little cookies.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops and place in baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops.
Cover and refrigerate minimum 8 hours.
Bake in marinade in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cake upside-down or earthquake
directions: Place pecans in bottom of greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions on box and pour over pecans.
Mix margarine, confectioners sugar and cream cheese. Drop by spoonfuls over cake.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes, or until done.

title: wynelle's gourmet rice crispy bars
directions: Combine light corn syrup, brown sugar and dash of salt in saucepan.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and cereal.
Mix well.
Press into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour chips into microwave dish and cover.
Nuke on High for 3 minutes.
Remove promptly and stir until all chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Spread on Rice Krispies.
Cool in refrigerator for approximately 1 hour or until chocolate is set.

title: low-fat muffins(low calorie)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into muffin pans, using either a nonstick pan or paper liners.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Add 2 boxes Pepperidge Farm seasoned croutons and stir.
Pour mixture over croutons and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a large saucepan, bring rice, milk and raisins to a full rolling boil.
Watch carefully, then remove from heat.

title: the stuff
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add to canned mixture.
Season to taste.

title: wild duck delite
directions: Take ducks and split down backs.
Put potatoes and onions in carcasses.
Put salt and pepper on.
Mix Texas Pete and Worcestershire sauce; put on ducks.
Wrap all in aluminum foil; put in oven and bake for 8 hours at 250°.
Will serve 3 to 4 people.

title: individual pot roast(no pot, no plate)
directions: Cut meat into strips; dice potato.
Pile everything on 1 (10 x 12-inch) piece aluminum foil and seal tightly.
Place in 350° oven or closed grill for 45 minutes, turning at least once.
Eat with spoon or pour off juices and eat with fingers.
May be prepared and frozen ahead of time for camping or sailing.
Store in cooler and cook when conditions allow.
Makes 1 serving.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl; whisk or beat with spoon until thick.
Equally good on tossed fresh veggies or fresh cut cole slaw.
Refrigerate to store.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix milk with soup.
Drain beans.
Mix all together except onions.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Put French fried onions on top and bake for 5 minutes.

title: fruit and rice salad
directions: Combine rice, pineapple, marshmallows and sugar. Toss gently. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Fold in apples, cherries and nuts. Fold in whipped topping. Chill 1 hour.
Makes 18 servings.

title: banana breeze
directions: Melt butter, sugar and cinnamon in saucepan.
Mix in crumbs. Put in pie pan and chill.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix together jello, water, onion juice, salt and vinegar; chill.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar well.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add flour and milk alternately. Beat with mixer 2 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into batter. Bake in 2 layer pans or oblong pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: french onion cube steak
directions: Cut
cube steak into strips.
Batter in flour, salt and pepper; brown
in
melted margarine.
Put in a shallow pan and pour the
French
onion soup over the cubed steak.	Cover with foil and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mrs. fields' cookies
directions: Mix in order given. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes (do not overbake).
Makes 75 to 80 medium size cookies.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts and shred in 9 x 12-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Chop onion over chicken.
Cube Velveeta cheese and add to that.
Next, crush 1/2 the Doritos and sprinkle over dish.
(May take more than 1/2 to cover.)

title: millionaire pie
directions: Have crust ready to fill before starting.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cream butter and sugar. Beat in egg yolks.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate.
Beat in flour and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into batter and mix.
Pour batter into 3 (9-inch) layer pans, lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: a beano buffet bean bake
directions: *Made available to those who need to reduce the gas-producing effects of dried beans.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend last 4 ingredients.
Fold in broccoli.
Put into a casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apple pie(sugar-free)
directions: Mix together dry ingredients. Pour over apples and mix well. Place mixture in unbaked crust. Sprinkle milk over top. Dot with margarine. Cover with top crust (seal well around edges). Bake in a 400° oven for 50 minutes. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Bring 6 cups of water to a boil.
Add broccoli and onion; cook until done.
Add everything else except flour and 1/2 cup of water.
Mix these in a bowl on the side.
Cook until cheese is melted, then add flour and water mixture to thicken.
Cook for about 10 extra minutes.

title: crispie recipe
directions: Place cereal in a bowl.
Add sugar, butter and syrup to a saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes; remove from heat and add condensed milk.
Boil additional 3 minutes.
Pour over crisp rice; mix well. Spray Pam into mold (1 time only).
Fill mold with mixture. Press in.
Remove to wax paper; allow to set 1 hour.
Seal in plastic wrap.

title: magic cookies bar
directions: Melt butter; add graham cracker crumbs and mix well.
Press mixture in bottom of pan.
Pour sweetened milk evenly over crumbs. Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: low-fat fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken breasts; rinse and pat dry.
Brush chicken with skim milk; roll in crumb mixture and coat both sides. Place chicken, meat-side up, on a foil-lined baking dish.
Season with salt if desired.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place in baking pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli pie
directions: Put frozen broccoli in water to thaw.
Grease deep pie pan. Put broccoli, chicken, onion and 2/3 cheese in pan.
Mix eggs, milk, Bisquick and seasonings; beat 1 minute.
Pour over mix in pan.
Bake 30-40 minutes in 400° oven, until knife comes out clean.
Spread rest of cheese on top.
Return to oven to melt.

title: uncle jim's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in molasses.

title: crab rolls
directions: Melt cheese and 2 sticks butter in microwave.
Stir until cheese and butter are mixed well.
Add crab mix to this.
Take bread and cut crust off of each slice.
Roll with rolling pin each slice and spread mix on bread; roll up.
Place in pan side by side. Before baking, brush with butter and broil and bake until brown. Can use sesame seed on top.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain the salmon well and flake; also crush bones and leave in.
Beat the egg and add to the salmon.
Add salt, pepper, onion, lemon juice and cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Shape into croquettes. Roll the croquettes in flour.
Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together and save 1 1/2 cups for topping.
Mix last 3 ingredients together.
Add to first mixture. Pour in cake pan.
Spread crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cook slightly.
Heat all ingredients and pour over carrots; cover.
Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat all together and pour into greased 2-quart casserole.

title: cottage cheese dumplings
directions: Chop the onion and pepper into small pieces.
Chop cilantro or parsley leaves finely.
Mix all the ingredients in a bowl.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water with salt and pepper until done.
Chop chicken.
In mixing bowl, combine chicken, water chestnuts, onions, sesame seeds, almonds and poppy seeds.
In another bowl, combine sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and oil.
Mix or shake well.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Refrigerate for 3 - 4 hours or overnight.
Before serving, toss with noodles and lettuce.

title: texas chili con carne
directions: Wash the beans; cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let soak for 1 hour.
Drain; add fresh water to cover.
Bring to a boil.
Cook over low heat 1 1/2 hours or until beans are almost tender.
Drain, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Cut the meat into 1/4-inch dice.
Heat the oil in a skillet; saute the onion and garlic 5 minutes.
Add the meat; cook until browned, stirring frequently.
Transfer to a casserole or saucepan.
Blend in the flour, then add tomatoes, salt, chili powder and bean water.
Bring to boil; cover.
Cook on low heat 1 1/2 hours.
Add beans.
Re-cover and cook 30 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Place in bowl and garnish with paprika and parsley.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large mixing bowl. Pour into greased 9 inch pie plate. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Allow to cool 10 minutes before slicing into pie wedges.

title: my own baked beans
directions: Brown onions and hamburger. Fry bacon and crumble. Mix catsup and brown sugar.
Put all beans in baking dish and mix in onions, hamburger, bacon, brown sugar and catsup mixture.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
It is best if you use all the types of beans called for, even if you don't like them.
You will in this dish.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown onion, beef and pepper in pan.
Add ketchup and relish. Simmer for 25 minutes.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Gradually add sugar to softened cream cheese.
Beat until fluffy.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Fold cheese mixture into Cool Whip.
Fill paper cup-lined cupcake tins. Freeze.

title: home canned tomato juice
directions: After tomatoes are quartered, cook for 5 to 10 minutes longer. Press through sieve.
Measure 7-quarts juice.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt to juice.
Mix well and pour into sterilized jars.
Seal. Process in pressure cooker for 10 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.

title: beef soup
directions: Brown beef with onion and drain.
Add vegetables, broth, tomatoes, water and spices.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add noodles. Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: low-fat cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: festive fudge m&m bars
directions: Combine oats, flour, nuts, sugar, soda and salt; mix well. Add margarine; mix and reserve 1 1/2 cups.
Press remainder into bottom of greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Melt shortening until warm.
Add 1 cup candies; continue cooking, stirring with spoon to break hard shell of M&M's.
Stir in condensed milk; spread over partially baked crust to within 1 inch of edge.
Combine remaining crumbs and candies. Sprinkle over top. Continue baking 20 minutes.

title: rice dish
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Add sour cream and green chilies.
Mix well.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° until thoroughly heated.

title: chili con carne(6 servings)
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Add tomato, seasonings and beans.
Simmer about 20 minutes or until thick.

title: spinach salad
directions: Place spinach leaves in salad bowl and toss with dressing. Just before serving, crumble bacon and sprinkle over top along with the hard-boiled eggs.

title: chinese clusters
directions: Place chocolate and butterscotch chips in 1 1/2 to 2 quart casserole.
Heat on level 6 for 3 1/2 minutes or until melted. Stir until smooth.
Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoons on to waxed paper.
Let set until firm.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender, pick off bone.
Mix stuffing with butter. Put a layer of stuffing in pan, then a layer of chicken and add mushroom soup.
Add a little more stuffing and chicken.
Put cream of chicken over it.
Put the rest of stuffing over top.
Put a little of the broth of chicken you cooked over to make it juicy.
Cook at 400° for 45 minutes to an hour until it's done.

title: mocha cookie delights
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together margarine, sugar and instant coffee.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet or nonstick pans.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove cookies and cool on wire racks.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: one bowl buttercream frosting
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat butter until creamy and fluffy. Add sugar and cocoa alternately with milk.
Beat until spreading consistency.
Blend in vanilla.
Makes 2 cups.

title: tuna chipper casserole
directions: Empty soup into 1-quart casserole.
Add milk and stir.
Drain tuna and add.
Crush potato chips and add all but 1/2 cup to soup mixture.
Add peas and stir.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top of casserole.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mom bass' homemade chili
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Saute onions and peppers in small amount of grease.
Mix these in a pot with tomato soup, chili powder and beans.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over hot spaghetti.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello with pineapple.
Heat slowly until jello is thoroughly dissolved.
Set aside to cool.
Add buttermilk to jello when cool and chill in refrigerator until just slightly thickened. Then add the other ingredients to this mixture.
Pour into large Pyrex dish (9 x 13) and chill overnight.
Very good.

title: jim's easy brunswick stew
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, drain. Add cooked pork and chicken. Add all other ingredients. Stir frequently. Simmer for approximately 1 - 1 1/2 hours. Serve over cooked rice. Great with crackers or cornbread muffins.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle each slice with salt; place in a bowl.
Let stand 30 minutes; drain well. Dip each slice in egg; coat with cracker crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Place half the eggplant in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread half the Quick Italian Sauce over slices.
Top with half the Mozzarella cheese and half the Parmesan cheese; repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until mixture is thoroughly heated.
Serve over vermicelli, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: west indies salad
directions: Put salt and lemon pepper on crab meat.
Add onion, oil, vinegar and water.
Let stand for several hours.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil; add egg and beat well.
Add applesauce and mix well.
Add dry ingredients by folding into other mixture. Do not overbeat.
Add vanilla and raisins.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: squash pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender or mix thoroughly with a spoon. Pour into an uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until center tests done and crust is brown, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sandymush beans
directions: In large ovenproof pot, cook onions, celery and garlic in a little olive oil until soft.
Cut meat from chicken bones and add to onion mixture.
Add all other ingredients and bake for 2 hours at 300°, stirring occasionally.
To prepare on stove top, simmer slowly for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.
Add chicken broth if mixture becomes too dry.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: hot chicken salad(serves 6)
directions: Combine all ingredients but cheese and potato chips.
Put into greased casserole (1 1/2-quart size).
Top with cheese and chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt brown sugar, margarine or butter and milk to boiling in a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool until slightly thick. Stir occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Gradually stir in powdered sugar with spoon.
If needed, stir in 2 or 3 teaspoons of water.

title: tennessee whiskey sauce
directions: Combine water, sugar and nutmeg and boil.
Combine whiskey and cornstarch.
Stir into sugar mix and cook until thick, then blend in butter.

title: cabbage salad with apples or pineapple(venezuela)
directions: Note:
For the pineapple you can use either canned or natural ones.
You can also make this salad with both apples and pineapple together.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Dissolve bouillon in hot water. In a small bowl, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar, soy sauce, bouillon and 6 tablespoons of pineapple juice. Stir until smooth; set aside.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in cold water.
Mix Crisco, sugar, salt and boiling water.
Add beaten eggs.
Add yeast mixture to Crisco mixture.
Cover and store in refrigerator 24 hours or overnight.

title: apple cranberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine sugars, flour and cinnamon.
Add fruit; mix well.
Turn into pastry-lined pan. Dot with margarine.
Cover and cut slits in top of crust.
Seal edges.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Trim broccoli and parboil for about 6 minutes until tender; arrange in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients, pour over broccoli.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: bluefish andalouse
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread 1 tablespoon oil on bottom of baking dish, large enough to hold the fillets in one layer. Arrange the fillets skin side down in the dish.
(If large fillets, cut into 2 or 3 pieces).
Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in saucepan and add onion, garlic, green pepper, saffron, bay leaf and thyme.
Cook, stirring often for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, vinegar and parsley.
Cook another 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Ladle the sauce over the fish.
Bring to boil on top of stove.
Place in the oven and bake for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand in the marinade until cool.
Chill, if desired.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: cream apple pie
directions: Mix together and crumble on top of pie.
Bake 10 minutes or longer at 400°.

title: lemonade pies
directions: Mix ingredients together, beat well.
Pour into crusts and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: beef burgundy
directions: One tablespoon oil, 2 tablespoons wine, lite salt and pepper and garlic powder, add meat marinade in small bowl in fridge one hour.
Cut meat across the grain into 1 1/2-inch thick strips. Brown in remaining oil until just past medium.
Put in mushrooms, just enough to warm them.
Add 1 cup water and 1 cup wine.
Take off fire to add gravy mix.
Put back on fire; add onions and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: rolled oats bread
directions: Bring water to boil; add salt, oats, oleo and molasses.
Cool. Add yeast which has been dissolved in the 1/2 cup warm water. Add flour and beat well.
Knead on floured board.
Put in greased bowl and let rise double in bulk.
Make into 2 loaves.
Put in loaf pans.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Bread needs to set a good hour before it can be cut.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water according to package directions.
Drain broccoli and spread it in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken, soup, mayonnaise, mushrooms, curry powder and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese in a medium bowl.
Spread chicken mixture over broccoli.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese over top.
Cover dish with foil and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove foil and stir; bake 10 to 20 minutes more. Can be frozen and served later.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and brown 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients and reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, until chicken is tender and sauce has thickened.
Serve over pasta.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream
together shortening, sugar, eggs and sour cream; add vanilla.
Sift
together dry ingredients and add to first mixture. Drop
by
teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass that's been dipped in sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mincemeat turnovers
directions: Combine cream cheese with butter.
Stir in flour.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Roll out on lightly floured surface to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut in 2 inch rounds.
Drop about 2 teaspoons mincemeat on each round.
Rub a little beaten egg around half edge, fold over and seal, allowing room to expand as it cooks.
Arrange on ungreased baking sheet and chill 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°. Brush turnovers lightly with melted butter.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes. Cool completely before storing.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Using half the spaghetti, chicken, cheese and mushrooms, make 2 layers in that order in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Dissolve broth mixture in water and thicken with flour.
Pour over spaghetti mix and bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes.
Lo-cal dish.

title: angel cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
For easier slicing and shaping work with half roll of well chilled dough at a time.
Refrigerate remaining dough until needed.
Slice dough into 1/4-inch slices.
For each angel, cut narrow strip from 2 sides of slice, forming a triangle. Roll strips into ball.

Place triangle on ungreased cookie sheet. To form wings, place 2 pretzels on either side of top point of triangle, making sure single hold side of pretzel touches dough. Place ball on top of triangle to form head; press with finger to flatten.
Repeat with remaining dough slices and pretzels, placing 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 11 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Decorate as desired.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: chicken wings pacifica
directions: Arrange wings or drumettes in shallow baking dish or pan. Heat butter or margarine, soy sauce, sugar, water and mustard until butter and sugar melt.
Cool.
Pour over wings.
Marinate at least 2 hours, turning once or twice.
Bake in same dish or pan at 375° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into individual serving dishes or large serving bowl.
Chill 30 minutes.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: apple sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with fork.
Press into a small greased rind mold.
Bake on a cookie sheet to avoid splatters. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Drain off excess fat.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 4 cups hot water; bring to a boil.
Add sugar while hot.
Mix juices and add 1 gallon water.
Add jello mixture. Makes 2 gallons.

title: hungarian crackling biscuits
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together, then rub in cracklings. Combine eggs, sour cream and water.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix lightly to form a soft dough, but firm dough.
Roll out on a floured board to 1/2-inch.
Cut with a small, round cookie cutter. Make impressions on top with knife crisscross fashion and place on a cookie sheet 1/2 inch apart.
Brush top with beaten egg and bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: golden hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal and onion.
Add milk and egg, stirring well. Carefully drop batter by tablespoon into deep hot oil (370°). Cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Fry until hush puppies are golden brown (3 to 5 minutes).
Drain well on paper towels. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: corn salad
directions: Toss, chill and serve.

title: pickled "uncooked" cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Spoon into jars.
(A used
mayonnaise jar will work well.)
Place plastic or foil over mouth of jar before tightening cover.
First day, turn jars upside-down.
Stand on top.
Second day, turn jars right side up.
Third day, turn jars upside-down. Fourth day, enjoy with sandwich.
Nice with hamburgers, meat loaf, baked beans, chicken salad, etc.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spread hash browns in casserole dish.
Spread onion, cheese, chicken soup and sour cream as evenly as possible on top of hash browns.
Crush cornflakes in your hands and spread evenly. Sprinkle melted margarine on top.
Cover with foil.
Cut slits in foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil the last 5 minutes to brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In skillet, brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add tomatoes and simmer.
In large saucepan, boil water.
Add noodles and salt; cook until tender.
Drain.
Add meat mixture to noodles. Pour into large baking dish.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake in oven until cheese melts.
Yields 4 or 5 servings.

title: o'henry bars(candy)
directions: Bring Karo syrup and sugar just to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, stir until all melted.
Add Special K cereal. Pack firmly in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Press with your fingers.
Melt chocolate and peanut butter chips over low heat in small pan.
Spread over mixture in pan.
Let set.
Cut and enjoy.

title: blueberry orange muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare 12 medium muffin cups.
Combine dry ingredients.
Gently stir in blueberries.
Add combined remaining ingredients, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: stir-fry
directions: Clean chicken and cut into cubes.
Saute in soy sauce.
Put 1/4 cup of oil in frying pan.
Add chicken.
Cook chicken until done.
Add chopped vegetables.
Add water and stir-fry sauce. Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 4 to 6.

title: wine jellies(makes 4 cups)
directions: In a stainless steel pan, stir the sugar into the wine. Heat over low to medium heat until the sugar is dissolved. Don't overheat. Bring almost to a simmer. Remove from heat and stir in the liquid pectin, dissolving completely. Pour into 8-ounce jelly jars. Keep refrigerated up to about 2 months.

title: mama sue's stew
directions: Heat oil, add stew meat and let brown.
Put in chopped onion and garlic, sprinkle flour over and stir occasionally at low heat. Add 2 cups water, salt, Worcestershire, rosemary, pepper and bouillon cubes. Stir.
Add remaining two cups of water.
Cover and cook on low heat 1-1/2 to 2 hours.
Add potatoes, carrots and celery (and if necessary a little more water) and let cook 30-45 minutes.
Put peas in at the end.
Serves 6-8.

title: pumpkin-oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat eggs, add pumpkin and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients.
Add oats, coconut, nuts and raisins, alternately with dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together in saucepan chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter.
Pour 1/2 box of cereal into large mixing bowl.
Add half of the melted mixture and stir to make sure all cereal bits are covered.
Pour half of the powdered sugar into paper bag.
Add coated cereal and shake gently to coat cereal mixture well. Repeat with other half of ingredients.

title: pumpkin pudding(budin de calabaza)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 2-quart glass baking dish. Cook pumpkin rapidly in water and salt, covered, for 20 minutes. Drain and put pumpkin through a potato ricer.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Turn mixture into baking dish and bake about 40 minutes.

title: southwestern tortilla wedges
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix tomato salsa and sour cream.
Reserve half of salsa mix.
Mix the remaining half with half the bell pepper and the chicken.
Place 2 tortillas on ungreased cookie sheet; spread with chicken mixture.
Spread 2 more tortillas with refried beans and guacamole.
Top stacks with remaining salsa, bell pepper and cheese.
Bake for about 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted and filling is hot.
Cut each stack into 8 wedges.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-cooked eggs in half lengthwise.
Put yolks in a bowl, mash with a fork.
Add Miracle Whip, mustard and vinegar; mix well.
Add sugar starting with 2 tablespoons until desired taste.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add onion salt or garlic salt if desired for more taste.
Stuff egg white halves with yolk mixture.
(Can fill plastic baggie with yolk mixture and cut one corner off to fill egg white halves.)
Garnish with paprika.

title: vegetarian refried beans
directions: Soak the beans overnight or bring to a boil.
Cover and let stand for an hour.
Drain.
Cover beans with water.
Bring to a boil and lower for a continual simmer.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish (except margarine).
Lay stick of margarine on top of everything and cover dish with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° until rice is done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put hash browns, soup, sour cream, cheese and 1 stick margarine and mix good.
Pour into large baking dish.
Top with crushed cornflakes and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Soften butter and shortening and add to mixture.
Add eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly; cut into squares.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix and Jell-O.
Add the oil and water. Beat for 3 minutes. Add the eggs and beat for 3 minutes more. Add the strawberries.
Bake in two layer pans in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: first base casserole
directions: Mix altogether; cover with cheese (American singles or mild Cheddar, shredded).
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 20 minutes.
Good to serve with chicken.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Add salad dressing to mixture prior to serving, otherwise raisins will get mushy.

title: rock candy
directions: Bring to 300 degrees on candy thermometer. Remove from heat, stir in flavorings and colorings. Pour into cold buttered iron skillet. Break and roll in powdered sugar when cool.

title: bacon spread
directions: Cook bacon; drain well and crumble.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Add green pepper and onion.
Stir in crumbled bacon and place in pie plate.
Top with walnuts.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: crock-pot chicken oriental
directions: Take skin off chicken.
Mix all other ingredients.
Place it all in crock-pot and cook approximately 7 hours at low setting. Turn chicken occasionally.
Serve with rice.

title: wurstfest sausage roll
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine shortening, sugar, salt, hot tap water and eggs.
Beat well.
Add yeast mixture.
Add 2 cups flour and beat well.
Stir in another 2 to 2 1/2 cups flour to make soft dough.
Refrigerate in large covered bowl overnight.
Divide dough into 3 portions.
Roll portion into circle 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in 2-inch circles.
Simmer sausage in covered pan approximately 5 minutes.
Place sausage piece in center of each circle.
Moisten edges of dough with a little water.
Lap one side of dough over sausage and press edge of dough together to seal.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Place rolls on greased cookie sheet.
Let rise about 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until doubled.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 12 minutes or until brown. Makes 36 rolls.

title: baked german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain on paper towels. Drain off fat.
Return 1/4 cup to skillet.
Add celery and onion and cook 1 minute.
Blend in flour.
Stir in water and vinegar; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and bubbly. Stir in sugar, salt and pepper.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small bite size pieces.
This will possibly take about 2 months.
Please save the trunk, you will need something to store the pieces in.
Add brown gravy to cover meat in pot.
Cook over a wood or kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve about 3,900 people.
If more are expected, the 2 rabbits may be added.
But do this only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended. Add remaining ingredients except the nuts. Mix well. Chill. Shape into balls. Roll in nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Beat 2 beaten eggs, sugar and cream cheese together and pour over crust.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 envelope unflavored gelatin which has been dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water. Cool.
Beat 3 egg whites, add 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat again.
Fold into cooled pumpkin mixture.
Pour over cooled crust and chill for 1 hour.
Great with Cool Whip.

title: bean pot soup
directions: Wash the beans.
Add to the water and bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat and let the beans soak for 1 hour. Simmer the beans for 20 minutes. Add tomatoes, celery, carrot, potato, rice, onion, bouillon cube, salt and pepper.
Brown the ground beef in shortening.
Bring soup to a boil.
Add the meat. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Add juices to the pudding; cook until thickened.
Pour over the mixed fruit.

title: broccoli-carrot casserole(microwave)
directions: Defrost the broccoli on paper towel at High power for 2 minutes or until spears can be separated; set aside in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix soup, sour cream, flour, carrots, onion, salt and pepper.
Cut broccoli into 1-inch pieces and stir into soup mixture.
Cook, covered, at High for 3 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Place margarine in 2-cup glass measure and heat 30 seconds or until melted.
Stir in stuffing and spoon over broccoli.
Cook, uncovered, at High for 4 to 5 minutes or until hot.
Top with cheese.
Total cooking time:
10 to 12 minutes.

title: scalloped potato casserole(makes 10 servings)
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, butter, green onions and 1 cup cheese in a lightly greased, deep 3-quart casserole dish.
Gently stir in potatoes, salt and pepper.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese and the crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: macadamia nut cream pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add egg yolks, stirring until well blended. Stir in milk slowly. Cook over low heat in double boiler, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add butter and vanilla. Cool thoroughly.
Pour into baked pie shell. Garnish with cream and Macadamia nuts.

title: nut cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook for about 1 hour at 325°.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, beat egg yolks. Stir in sweetened milk, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into pie crust.

In a small bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff. Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form. Spread on top of pie and bake 15 minutes or until meringue is golden. Cool before serving.

title: "dolmathes" - stuffed grape leaves
directions: Rinse leaves in cold water.
Combine ground meat with remaining ingredients.
Place 1 teaspoon filling in center of a grapevine leaf (ribbed side) and shape in narrow roll.
(May be frozen at this point.)

title: chicken spitzata
directions: Brown chicken with onions and garlic.
Add olives, mushrooms, seasoning, wine and water.
Simmer 1 hour; remove cover and cook until wine cooks down.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: old fashion stuffed cabbage
directions: Cut off bottom of cabbage, about 1 inch, and remove entire core.
Remove any damaged leaves, rinse and place whole head into salted boiling water.
Allow to return to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 25 minutes.
Drain.
Allow to cool sufficiently for handling.

title: dilly cheese ring
directions: Cheddar cheese or Colby/Jack mixture can be substituted for Parmesan.

title: prudence island apple icing
directions: Combine all ingredients
together.
Beat
with mixer at slow speed, gradually
increasing to medium.
Beat until thick and smooth and all graininess has disappeared.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla and beat until light; stir while beating.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix.
Pour into two loaf pans, greased and bottom lined with waxed paper.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: blt bites
directions: Cut a thin slice off of each tomato top.
Scoop out and discard pulp.
Invert the tomatoes on a paper towel to drain.
In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into tomatoes.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Yield: 16 to 20 servings.

title: best waffles
directions: Put warm water in a large bowl; stir in dry yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Next melt butter in milk over low heat.
Add salt and sugar.
Add to yeast mixture.
Stir in flour.
Beat smooth.
Let stand overnight at room temperature.
Before baking, add eggs and soda.
Beat waffles.
Cook in a waffle iron.
Makes 4 waffles.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Heat cranberries, sugar and water to boiling, stirring often. Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of the food coloring and the cocoa.
Add to creamed mixture.
Sift together flour and salt, alternately add to batter with buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in vinegar and soda by hand.
Do not beat.
Pour into cupcake pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Decorate as desired.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: parsley grilled chicken
directions: Press 3/4 teaspoon pepper into meaty sides of chicken breasts.

title: chunky barbecue beef
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown meat in large skillet sprayed with vegetable pan spray.
Add remaining ingredients; mix.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake for 2 hours.
Water may be added, if desired.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Combine with onions, beef, pork, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into balls, about the size of walnuts.
In a large saucepan, combine chili sauce, water and grape jelly.
Heat to simmer.
Drop meatballs into sauce; simmer for about 1 hour. Skim off excess fat from top of sauce.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: farmer's salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in a large bowl in order given.
Spread the dressing over the lettuce.
Cover and store overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: big pot of soup(approximately 2 gallons)
directions: Simmer until veggies are cooked, chill and reheat. (It tastes better that way.)

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat egg white stiff, not dry.
Add sugar, spoonful at a time. Add vinegar and vanilla.
On well-greased pan, drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart.
Bake at 250° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: aunt peggy's shrimp amandine
directions: Shell and devein shrimp; cook in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook rice, drain and cool.
Saute peppers and onions in butter for 5 minutes.
Add undiluted soup, cream, mace, salt, pepper, sherry and almonds.
Turn into 1/2-quart casserole. Refrigerate.

title: three bean salad
directions: Bring to boil. Pour this over the vegetables and chill.

title: little cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat cream cheese in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Fill 6 lined muffin cups 3/4 full and bake for 30 minutes or until a knife blade comes out clean.
Serve plain or with fruit.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Beat eggs.
Add enough milk to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add dried onion.
Drain spinach well.
Spread in bottom of baked pie shell. Sprinkle with cheeses.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, covered.

title: sangria
directions: Mix and chill wine, orange juice, sugar, brandy and Cointreau. Add the soda.
Pour into a punch bowl over an ice ring.
Float the lemon and orange slices on top.
Recipe can be doubled easily. Yields 50 (4 ounce) servings.

title: carrot bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange carrots in ungreased baking dish. layer cauliflowerets over carrots.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cover and bake until vegetables are tender, 50 to 55 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Drain pineapple, chop walnuts, and whip the whipping cream, adding sugar to taste.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all with fork and season.
Place in buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with broken bits of potato chips.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°, or until brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In large bowl, mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Add banana. Beat with electric mixer until blended.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture.
Beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Line pie pan with pie crust.
Add milk to eggs.
Mix sugar, flour and nutmeg and stir into eggs.
Mix in rhubarb.
Pour in pan. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Spread chicken in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Cover with mixed vegetables.
Combine soup and broth; heat.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add margarine, then milk.
Pour over casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: prize-winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour; drain. Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, brown sugar and margarine.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Pour onto cooled pretzel crust, spreading evenly. Mix jello, water and strawberries.
Chill until slightly thickened, then pour over cream cheese layer.
Spread evenly. Chill in refrigerator until jello is set.

title: mini tacos
directions: Brown hamburger, shred cheese, shred lettuce, cut tomatoes and heat taco shells in microwave until warm.
Put all the stuff in the shell and you eat it!

title: corn bread with basil, red peppers and monterey
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Butter 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Melt 1 tablespoon butter in medium nonstick skillet over medium-low heat. Add onion and saut until tender, about 10 minutes. Cool. Mix cornmeal and next 5 ingredients in large bowl. Add 7 tablespoons butter and rub in with fingertips until mixture resembles coarse meal. Whisk buttermilk and eggs in medium bowl to blend. Add buttermilk to dry ingredients and stir until blended. Mix in red peppers, basil and onion. Transfer to prepared pan. Bake corn bread until golden and tester inserted into center comes out clean, about 45 minutes. Cool 20 minutes in pan on rack. Cut corn bread into squares.

title: grandma's corn pudding
directions: This recipe is listed and used as a side dish.
Serves 4 people.
Recipe may be doubled or tripled, etc. to serve different size groups.
For 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole dish, prepare X's 4.

title: pumpkin log
directions: Roll up and refrigerate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all except cornflakes.
Put in a 3-quart casserole. Spread cornflakes and margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs and butter.
Spread in greased pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Spread on top; sprinkle nuts and coconut on top of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 33 to 35 minutes.

title: raisin filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, sour cream, soda and vanilla.
Add flour; then mix and knead until stiff enough to roll.
Cut into cookies and place one round on cookie sheet,
Fill heaped up with raisins, then cover with another round; cut slit in center of top round for steam to escape.
Bake 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: black forest cake
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 1/2 cup juice.
Combine reserved cherry juice, cherries, granulated sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Add vanilla and stir.
Split each cake layer in half horizontally. Crumble one half layer, set aside.
Beat cold whipping cream and the confectioners sugar in large bowl with an electric mixer set at high speed until stiff peaks form.
Reserve1 1/3 cups whipped cream for decorative piping.
Place one cake layer on serving plate.
Spread with 1 cup whipped cream; top with 3/4 cup cherry topping.
Top with second cake layer, 1 cup whipped cream and 3/4 cup cherry topping; top with third cake layer.
Frost cake sides with remaining whipped cream; pat gently with reserved cake crumbs.
Spoon reserved 1 1/2 cups whipped cream into pastry bag fitted with star tip; pipe around top and bottom edges of cake. Spoon remaining cherry topping over top of cake.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix the tomatoes, soups, Velveeta cheese and onion.
Put a layer of chicken, a layer of chips and layer of the mixed ingredients.
Sprinkle with chili powder (optional).
Make two layers of each.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cover loosely with foil to prevent chips from burning.

title: orange oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour with salt and soda and set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add orange juice, orange rind and vanilla and mix well.
Stir in flour mixture.
Add oatmeal, dates and nuts.
Drop from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: quick louisiana pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for the vanilla.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Beat until creamy consistency; drop quickly on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O with the boiling water.
Stir until Jell-O is dissolved. Add the applesauce. Stir well.
Add the strawberries. Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Use whipping cream, if desired.

title: guacamole
directions: After peeling and removing seeds from avocados, mash them to desired consistency.
Add all ingredients.
Use as much mayonnaise as needed.
Chill and serve.

title: cheese log
directions: Season cheese with garlic powder to taste.
Roll cheese in shape of a log.
Roll log in chili powder.
Chill 1/2 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with food coloring and cocoa, then add to mix.
Add salt and flour with buttermilk and vanilla, alternately add soda and vinegar.
Don't beat hard; just blend.
Bake in 2 (8 or 9-inch) round pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In heavy, 2-quart saucepan, heat whipping cream, sugar, chocolate and corn syrup over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil, stirring occasionally. Cook 4 to 5 minutes longer until sauce thickens slightly (mixture should be gently boiling), stirring constantly. Remove pan from heat. Stir in margarine and vanilla until smooth. Serve immediately or cool completely. Cover and refrigerate. Do not cover sauce until it is cold. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: easy applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan.
Beat cake mix, applesauce and eggs in a large bowl on low for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in raisins. Pour into pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool inverted on a wire rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: crumb cake(coffee cake)
directions: Combine sugar, flour and all other ingredients, except the milk.
Save 1/2 cup dry ingredients to put on top.
Add milk; pour in pan.
Top with the 1/2 cup dry mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: zucchini dinner salad
directions: Quarter zucchini lengthwise and slice thinly.
Slice celery with leaves.
Cut tomatoes into wedges.
Slice onions and tops. Add cooked beans; toss with salad dressing.
Pile salad into lettuce cups and garnish with radish roses or alfalfa sprouts.

title: glazed ham loaves
directions: Preheat oven to moderate 350°.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine ham, beef, crumbs, milk, eggs, vinegar, sugar, flour and dry mustard in bowl.
Divide mixture into 10 portions.
Shape each into 5 x 2 x 2-inch loaf.
Arrange in greased pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes.

title: party pear salad
directions: Over-stuff pear half with mixture of cream cheese, pecans, ginger and juice.
Place other half over the stuffed half of pear. Add sprig of mint to small end.
Dilute red food coloring and drop on paper towel.
Gently rub colored towel over hump of pear. Place on lettuce leaf.

title: quick mexican chicken and dumplings
directions: Saute meat, onions and bell peppers in butter in a large pot. Add remaining ingredients, except tortillas.
Bring to a boil. Cut flour tortillas into sixths.
Drop into liquid, one at a time. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot oil in Dutch oven.
Add 1 cup water and tomato sauce.
Simmer 1 hour, covered. May need to add water.

title: broccoli  and cheese
directions: Cut thick stem off bottom of broccoli.
Break and separate. In a large sauce pan bring salt water to boil.
Blanch broccoli for 5 minutes. Drain well.
Melt Velveeta in microwave
Pour over broccoli and serve hot.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add red or green food coloring and add 1/2 bottle Certo.
Allow to sit 5 minutes.
Put in jars and paraffin. Serve with cream cheese and crackers.

title: walnut crescents
directions: Cream the butter, vanilla and sugar.
Add water and flour; mix thoroughly.
Stir in walnuts.
Form into crescents or 1/2 of a circle, about 2-inches.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 15 or 20 minutes at 300°.

title: pumpkin coffee cake
directions: Cream 1/2 cup butter, 3/4 cup sugar and 3 eggs. Add vanilla. Mix in flour, baking powder and baking soda. Add sour cream. Set batter aside. Stir together pumpkin, remaining egg and sugar. Stir in pie spice and set aside. Prepare streusel by combining brown sugar, 1/3 cup butter, cinnamon and nuts. Set aside. Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick vegetable spray and spoon in half the batter. Layer on half the streusel, then all pumpkin mixture. Spread on the remaining batter, then top with remaining streusel mixture. Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean. Makes 15 servings.

title: hamburger and cabbage stew
directions: Brown meat.
Pour off fat.
Add salt, garlic powder, onion salt and soy sauce.
Put in large pot.
Add juice and beef bouillon cubes.
Add meat and cabbage.
Simmer 1 hour.
Can add a little sugar for sweeter sauce.

title: fruited rice with cinnamon
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, heat margarine on high 30 seconds. Add almonds and onions and microwave on High for 1 minute, stirring once until onions are tender.
Add broth, apricots and raisins and microwave on High 2 minutes until rice is heated through.
Add cinnamon, salt and pepper.
Serves 4.
Contains 161 calories, 3 gm fat and 144 mg sodium.

title: candied carrots
directions: Cook carrots, covered, in a small amount of boiling water, just until tender, about 6 to 10 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Prepare oven to 350°.
Dump undrained pineapple into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Spread evenly.
Dump in pie filling and spread into even layer.
Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer. Spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Put butter over top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm or cooled.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Cook rice.
Mix all ingredients; bake in casserole dish for 1/2 hour at 325°.

title: chocolate peanut candy(makes 3 dozen)
directions: Melt chips over a double boiler.
Pour peanuts into foiled ice cube trays.
Pour in chocolate.
Store in refrigerator until solid.

title: cheese and ham strata
directions: Cover bottom of a buttered 9 x 13 casserole with 8 slices of bread. Fit slices closely, trimming if necessary. Place bite-size pieces of ham on bread. Add slices of cheese. Cover with 8 remaining slices of bread.

title: mushroom delight
directions: Lightly saute mushrooms in butter, remove from heat and reserve.
Saute onion, celery and green pepper until tender, about 5 minutes.
Place half of buttered bread cubes in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Add the cooked vegetables including the mushrooms.
Cover with the remaining bread cubes.
In separate bowl, beat the eggs, stirring in the mayonnaise and milk to blend well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in casserole.
Spread soup on top and sprinkle with grated cheese. Top with buttered crumbs.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with cold ham or chicken slices.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: browned cream potatoes
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter in saucepan; stir in flour. Gradually add cream and cook, stirring constantly until sauce bubbles and thickens.
Add salt, pepper, onion and nutmeg; blend thoroughly.
Add potatoes to the sauce and mix well.
Pour into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Dot top with remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes until browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Mix until smooth.
Roll into nickel-size balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put nut on top of each ball and press down.
Cook at 300° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 1/2 to 7 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer chicken.
Mix 1 cup broth, sour cream and chicken soup. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle vegetables over chicken.
Put 1 package Pepperidge Farm (large) dressing over top.
Mix cup broth and 1 stick of butter and pour over dressing. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ketchup and coke roast
directions: Put roast in skillet and brown (don't cook all the way), then add ketchup, Coke, onion and bell pepper.
Cook until roast is completely done.

title: ultimate cheesecake
directions: Cream the cheeses together. Add other ingredients and mix well. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into a 10-inch spring-form pan over graham crust.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 60 minutes. Turn oven off and allow to rest in oven 10 minutes before opening oven door. Cool cake in oven. Serve after 1 to 2 days for ripening of flavor.

title: leek soup
directions: Chop vegetables and add to chicken broth. Cook until tender. Put in blender or food processor on puree. Heat and serve. Good with a spoon full of sour cream on top.

title: cheesy beef macaroni
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain grease off.
Cook macaroni.
Add tomatoes and macaroni to meat.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add cheese; cook another 5 minutes.

title: make ahead coleslaw
directions: In large bowl, add vinegar, sugar, oil, green onions, mustard, salt and pepper sauce, mixing well. Add cabbage and carrot, tossing until well coated. Cover and refrigerate to meld the flavors (best after 24 hours). Will keep for 4 days. Serves 6 to 8.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Layer rice and corn.
Cover with 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 can water.
Layer green pepper, onion and ground beef.
Cover with 1 can tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water.
Cover mixture with bacon and bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake for 1/2 hour.

title: 10 minute chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet.
Add chicken breast strips.
Stir in Hidden Valley dressing. Mix to coat chicken. Add thawed out vegetables and water.
Stir-fry about 2 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve over rice.

title: blackberry mousse
directions: Combine berries, sugar and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Puree and set aside.
Put the water in a small saucer and sprinkle the gelatin over it. Set aside for a few minutes.
Stir the softened gelatin into the berry puree.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Place in goblets or in a souffle dish and refrigerate for at least an hour before serving.

title: chicken or turkey bake
directions: In bowl, add oleo to stuffing mix and water if needed.
Dilute soup with 1/2 cup milk.

title: hardtack candy
directions: Boil to 300°.
Add flavoring, oil and food coloring.
Pour on greased cookie sheet or marble.
Grease hands and scissors with butter and cut into pieces while hot.
One batch makes 6 jelly jars full.

title: cranberry orange punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine cranberry juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, add orange soda, liqueur and ice.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: easy no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla. Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours. Garnish with berries, if desired.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix with dry taco seasoning. Add shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, crushed Doritos, shredded cheese and French dressing.
Stir together.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender; drain, then add cheese, milk, salt and pepper. Mix. Bake in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan for 25 minutes at 400°. Cover with cheese slices (your choice) before serving while still hot.

title: greek spinach pie
directions: Cook spinach
and
onion together and drain (until very dry). Add
Feta
cheese,
cottage
cheese
and eggs, one at a time, beating
well after each.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Butter 9 x 13-inch dish.
Line with several sheets of buttered filo.
Top
with
spinach mixture.
Place 5 or 6 more sheets of buttered filo on top.

title: caesar salad
directions: Wash and dry lettuce. Tear into bite-size pieces.
Put in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients, except croutons, into blender.
Mix about 10 seconds.
Pour over lettuce, add croutons on top.
Serve.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, spices, salt, lemon juice and butter. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 30 or 40 minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Sprinkle soda over dates.
Add water and let stand.
Mix flour and salt together and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla, then add flour alternating with the date mixture. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix all other ingredients into a bowl. Layer casserole dish with torn tortillas.
Pour half of mixture over tortillas.
Then add generous layer of cheese.
Repeat the torn tortillas, mixture and cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: high fiber raisin bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder. Set aside.

title: cheesy beer soup
directions: Cook and stir onion and garlic in margarine in large saucepan on medium-high heat until tender.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Add cheese, milk, beer, Worcestershire sauce, and hot pepper sauce.

title: peanut butter and chocolate cookies
directions: In bowl, beat butter until light and creamy.
Beat in brown and granulated sugars.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until blended.
Beat in peanut butter.
Stir together the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Stir into peanut butter mixture. Stir in chocolate and peanut butter chips.
Spoon about 1/4 cup dough for each cookie onto lightly greased baking sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 14 to 16 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Let stand on baking sheet a few minutes, then remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate covered christmas balls
directions: Combine milk, sugar and oleo.
Add grated coconut and chopped pecans.
Roll into small balls and freeze hard.
Melt chocolate and wax in a double boiler.
Dip frozen balls into chocolate.
Let cool on waxed paper.
(Stick toothpick in ball to dip in chocolate and wax mixture.)
Let cool on waxed paper.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage.
Drain well.
Add soup.
Cover this with grated cheese.
Combine crackers with melted margarine and spread over top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mum salad
directions: Mix jello as directed on box and let cool.
Prepare Dream Whip as directed, then beat Dream Whip, cream cheese and salad dressing with mixer.
Stir in drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Take a knife and loosen edges of mixture. Pour jello over top of mixture.
Chill.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk.
Mix lightly to make soft dough.
Place on floured board.
Roll dough approximately 1/4 to 3/8-inch thickness.
Place on greased cooking sheet.
Bake at 450° for about 12 minutes.

title: brownie pizza pie
directions: Grease two 9-inch pie pans.
In a 3-quart saucepan, bring corn syrup and cream to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Add chocolate and stir until melted.
Set aside 2/3 cup of this chocolate mixture.
Add butter and sugar to remaining chocolate mixture and stir until butter is melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour, salt and nuts. Pour into pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until firm. Cool.
Serve topped with ice cream and chocolate sauce.

title: cheese chowder
directions: Dice all vegetables.
Cook together in enough water to barely cover until tender.
Add milk and cheese, pepper and salt and heat until cheese is melted.

title: mr. l's croissants
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Put on lettuce leaf on croissants.
Serves 2.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with nonstick spray.
In a large bowl, with mixer on medium, beat flour, 1 cup oleo, 1 cup sugar and salt.
Mixture will resemble fine crumbs.
Press firmly into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 23 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients and pour into pastry lined pie plate.
Bake in hot preheated oven at 425° for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 1 hour.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Beat on medium speed of mixer for 2 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients together lightly with a fork.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk. Mix well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
(May be baked in 8-inch layer pans.)
Cool.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pie shell.
Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate overnight.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meats and onions;
drain.
Layer ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan in
the
following
order:
refried
beans, meat mix, chilies, cheese and taco
sauce.
Bake
at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When
hot, put sour cream and guacamole on top of it. Dip in chips.

title: harvest loaf cake
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Combine flour with baking soda, salt and spices.
Cream butter in large mixing bowl. Gradually add sugar.
Cream at high speed of mixer until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Beat well.
At low speed, add dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin (begin and end with dry ingredients).
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate bits and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil butter, sugar and milk together for 9 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and chocolate chips. Beat until it thickens.
Pour in 2 large buttered pans.
Makes 4 pounds.

title: potato supreme
directions: Melt butter and mix with all of the ingredients, except for 1/3 of the Cheddar cheese.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until bubbly and cheese melts on top.

title: apple pie
directions: Crumb flour, shortening and brown sugar with fingers.
Press half of this mixture into pie tin bottom and sides.
Reserve remaining crumb mixture to be put on top of apples.
Peel apples and quarter them, layer them on crumb mixture in pie tin and making overlap each other.
Sprinkle white sugar and generous amount of cinnamon over apples.
Press remaining crumb mixture over apples.
Bake in moderate oven until apples are tender, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot with ice cream on top.

title: venison
directions: Sprinkle seasoned salt evenly on both sides of each steak. In a one-gallon zip lock bag, place the steaks and pour in the Italian dressing; seal.
Place the bag into a shallow baking dish. Marinate in refrigerator for 6 to 24 hours, turning bag once. Over medium hot coals, place steaks directly onto the grill for 8 minutes.
Turn and brush with marinade.
Grill for 8 to 10 minutes more.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put in baking dish and fan potatoes slightly.
Sprinkle with salt.
Drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.

title: country scrambled eggs
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook bacon over medium heat for 5 minutes. Add potatoes and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are browned and crispy-tender, 15 or 20 minutes.
Add onions and green pepper; continue cooking until crispy-tender, 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour off fat.

title: health bread
directions: Boil together raisins or chopped dates and water 5 minutes and cool.
Combine dry ingredients and add raisin mixture.
Pour into a greased 5 x 9 loaf pan and bake at 350° for about one hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients completely.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Cream together soft butter or oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add sour cream alternately with flour mixture.
Mix together to make batter.

title: louisiana baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onion until done and drain well.
Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves approximately 10 to 15.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and mix.
Add pumpkin, milk, salt and vanilla.
Cook over hot water until thick, stirring constantly (about 10 minutes).
Add gelatin.
Stir until thoroughly dissolved; cool.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add remaining sugar, gradually beating after each addition until stiff.
Fold in pumpkin mixture.
Beat 1/2 cup cream until stiff and fold into mixture.
Spoon into baked pie shell.
Chill several hours or overnight.
To serve, beat remaining cup of cream until stiff. Spread on top of filling.
Top with coconut.

title: karmel korn
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients. Stir until boiling.
Boil, without stirring, for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add the baking soda and vanilla. Stir a couple of times. Do not overstir.
Pour over the popped corn.
Bake 1 hour at 250°; stir every 15 minutes. Fits on 2 cookie sheets.

title: broccoli carrot soup
directions: In 3-quart microwave casserole, combine broccoli, carrots, onion and water. Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. In small bowl, stir soup until smooth. Stir in milk, cheese and seasonings. Mix well. Stir into veggie mixture. Cover. Microwave on High for 8 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring twice during cooking time. Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: mexican flavored casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add onion and green pepper; drain fat. Add soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes and Pet milk.
Crush the chips before opening the bag.
Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Put 1/3 of the chips in the dish, then a layer of hamburger mixture, then cheese. Repeat, ending with chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple-walnut-poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix together the oil and sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Set aside.

title: crispy asparagus
directions: Wash the asparagus; scrape.
Remove tough ends.
Cut into 2-inch pieces, including the spears and set aside.
In a skillet, roast sesame seed until they turn uniformly golden brown. Transfer to a bowl.
Warm butter in a skillet; add asparagus. Saute on medium-high heat.
Asparagus should remain crisp.
Add soy sauce.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Serve hot.
A great vegetable side dish.

title: powdered sugar icing
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the powdered sugar and butter or margarine.
Mix thoroughly with a spoon.
Stir in the vanilla and 2 tablespoons milk.
Stir in additional milk, one teaspoon at a time, until icing is smooth and drizzling consistency.

title: potato cakes(lumpe)
directions: Cook potatoes; mash while hot.
Combine with sugar, salt and margarine.
Let cool.
When cool, add flour and mix until it becomes a thick dough.
Pinch off a ball the size of an egg. Shape into a round, rolled pie crust.
Roll until paper thin on floured cloth.
Bake on electric griddle or frypan until spotted brown on both sides.
Remove and stack on foil; cover with towel. When cool, pack in plastic bags.
May be frozen.

title: goulash
directions: Trim
all
the fat from the meat; cut meat in 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Heat
the oil in a heavy saucepan or Dutch oven.
Brown the
meat in it.
Remove meat.
In the oil remaining, brown the onions.
Return
the
meat
and mix in the salt, pepper, garlic and
paprika
until
meat
is coated.
Add the water and tomato sauce.
Cover
and
cook
over low heat 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4, calories 315 per serving.

title: hamburger supper
directions: Place ground beef in glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pat down until bottom is covered.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Slice potatoes thin on top of beef.
Next, slice carrots on top of potatoes, then onion.
Add shredded cabbage to cover top and place pats of margarine over mixture.
Cover with foil.
A can of cream of mushroom soup makes a more delicious dish.

title: goulash
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
In blender, mix tomatoes, onion and liquid from green beans and salt. Mix all ingredients.
Pour into crock-pot and simmer several hours.
Serve topped with Cheddar cheese and crackers. Serves 3 to 4.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Batter must be thick and not runny. Fry in deep fryer until golden brown.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water two notches above 265° (hard ball stage).
Set off heat and let set until it stops bubbling.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Set for 2 hours and drain. Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Put in squash and let come to a boil.
Put in jars.
Add 2 red peppers for color, if you can find them, or use some pimientos in jar.

title: corky troutt's chicken casserole
directions: Note:
You can use one canned whole chicken or three 5 ounce cans chicken meat and 1 can chicken broth.
Also you can use 1 small package (3 x 6-inch) Uncle Ben's wild rice.

title: ginger snaps
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, then remaining ingredients.
Work with hands, if necessary.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place on an oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees 10 - 12 minutes.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add preserves, nuts and raisins.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Grease and flour pans.
Pour in prepared pans and bake until cake tests done, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fresh ginger-peach sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 4-cup glass measure.
Stir carefully. Cover and microwave on High for 5 to 8 minutes or until mixture is bubbly and peaches are cooked.
Stir halfway through.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over rhubarb in pie shell. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all together and shape into 1 large loaf or 2 smaller ones.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix well; roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar. Store in tight covered container.
Makes about 48.
Make a few days ahead.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into prepared Bundt pan. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and shredded Cheddar cheese until well blended.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Shape into ball and roll in finely chopped pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix and
chill	2
hours.
Roll
in small balls, put on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 9 day pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Pour syrup over them.
Next day, reheat syrup, pour over again.
Do this for 4 days.
On the 9th day, heat, put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook bacon crisp and take out and put on paper towel to drain.
Put the bread crumbs in bacon grease with onions and brown lightly.
Then put spinach and vinegar in and cook until dry. Form into balls.
Crumble bacon over them.
Slice eggs and put on balls.

title: sweet and sour smokeys
directions: Combine all ingredients, except hot dogs, in fondue pot or crock-pot.
Mix well.
Bring to boil.
Add hot dogs.
Reduce temperature.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: frying pan supper
directions: Fry the hamburger and onion until it changes color, then add the potatoes, cabbage and celery.
Sprinkle it with salt and pepper and add the water.
Cover and simmer it for 20 minutes or until the vegetables are done.

title: yankee doodle potato salad(makes 6 servings)
directions: In a large bowl, mix together first 6 ingredients.
Add potatoes.
Toss to coat.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or until ready to serve.

title: raisin bars
directions: Simmer, with lid on for 20 minutes, raisins, water and shortening.
Cool, then add egg and sugar.
Sift together and add flour, cinnamon, soda and nutmeg.
Stir together and add vanilla and nuts.
Bake 20 minutes in a long pan at 350°.
Cover with thin icing.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Stir in pecans and flour into mixture.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar; roll again when cool.

title: italian garden soup(yields 2 quarts)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter 5 minutes in large kettle. Add broth, vegetables, salt and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
May be garnished with croutons and/or Parmesan cheese. Quick and easy!

title: crispy brunch
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom with layer of Rice Krispies and sausage.
Sprinkle with dry onions, rice and Cheddar cheese.
At this point you can freeze for later use. Combine celery soup, eggs and milk.
Mix and pour over casserole. Sprinkle Rice Krispies over the top.
Put in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Season and flour chops.
Fry until nicely brown and done. Remove chops from pan and drain grease.
Add flour to small amount of grease left in skillet and brown into a roux.
Add sauerkraut to the roux and cook until hot and thick.
Serve with browned chops.

title: fudge
directions: Let stand to melt, not too long.
Mix and add nuts if desired and pour into greased pan.

title: delicious hot rolls
directions: Combine
first
four
ingredients.
Stir
until
cool. Second,
add remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Place in refrigerator for 4 hours.
Roll in any shape or just spoon out onto
greased pan and let rise for 3 hours.
The dough may be left in icebox as long as 10 days.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tortilla hot dish
directions: Brown beef, seasoned with salt and pepper, garlic powder and cumin.
Simmer.
Add soups, sauce and pepper.
Layer in casserole dish the crumbled tortillas, beef mixture and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecues
