directions: Brown hamburger and onion together. Add salt and pepper to taste. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in cup of water until tender. Brown hamburger in skillet. Mix ingredients with noodles and tomato soup. Add some salt.

title: mexican squash casserole
directions: Saute chiles and onion in butter.
Add squash and simmer till soft. Add corn.
Cover with Velveeta cheese and bake till melted.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, beat in milk, flour and coconut.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sea scallops with basil sauce
directions: Melt butter in heavy medium skillet over medium heat.
Add sliced mushrooms and minced shallots.
Saute until mushrooms are tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in dry vermouth; simmer 1 minute. Mix in flour.
Add clam juice and 1/4 cup water.
Cook until sauce thickens slightly, about 10 minutes.
Whisk in whipping cream. Puree basil leaves and sauce in blender until smooth.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cream together first 4 items.
Fold in Rice Krispies.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto wax paper on a cookie sheet. Refrigerate until firm.

title: buns
directions: Scald milk, add sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool until lukewarm.
Pour in large bowl.
Mix 2 cups flour into smooth paste. Add eggs and mix well, then add yeast and mix well.
Add rest of flour (2 1/2 cups).
Knead.
Put in greased bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Make into buns and let rise.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: corn patch spam bake
directions: Cook the 2 1/2 cups noodles in 2 quarts salted boiling water for 10 minutes; drain, then pour into deep 9-inch casserole.
Mix in drained corn, cream soup, milk, salt and 1-inch squares of Spam (use most of 1 can).
If desired, top with grated or shaved sharp cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place triangles of Spam around edge.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: red devil mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl and whisk until very smooth.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch round pans.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool 5 minutes in pan, then turn out and cool on wire racks.
Fill and frost top and sides with Devil's Food Fudge Frosting.

title: grandma giannelli's artichokes
directions: Using a sharp knife, cut the stem off each artichoke to make a flat base.	Pull off tough outer leaves.
Cut off about 1/2 inch off the top of each artichoke and open tops with your fingers. Invert the	artichokes
on	a flat surface, pressing down on each one
to
open
its	leaves.
Moisten
bread
with water.
Combine all other
ingredients
and
add to bread mixture.	Divide filling into
four	equal
parts
and stuff into artichokes, center first, then
add
some
filling between the leaves.

title: cheese balls with olive
directions: Mix cheese and flour. Add melted butter. Mix well. Form 1 teaspoon mixture around olive to shape into ball. Place on cookie sheet and chill for 1 hour.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute the broccoli and onion in melted margarine.
When tender, mix with cooked rice, soup, Cheez Whiz and canned mushrooms.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with crushed Ritz crackers that have been mixed with the melted margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tomato and garlic sauce
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan and cook onions until tender and transparent.
Stir in garlic powder and cook 1 minute.
Coarsely chop tomatoes in blender and add, along with remaining ingredients, to saucepan.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 3 cups.
May be used as pizza sauce or over pasta.

title: crimson pride cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil and add eggs.
Beat until real creamy. Add coloring to vinegar and set aside.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and soda together.
Add coloring mixture to sugar mixture. Alternately add flour mixture and buttermilk to sugar mixture. Add vanilla and mix well.
Bake in three layers at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Roll half of pastry; put in deep dish pie plate.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon, allspice and salt.
Add sugar mixture to apples; toss to coat apples.
Put apple mixture in pastry-lined dish; dot with butter.
Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edge. Cover edges with foil.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil; bake for 25 minutes more (until crust is golden).

title: maxine's navy bean soup
directions: Wash beans; bring to hard boil.
Set off heat for 1 hour.
Add ham bone and bay leaf.
Cook until beans are soft.
Add salt if needed.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box; add margarine and onion. When cooked, take from heat.
Add Spam, cream of celery and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Put in a casserole baking dish.
Put grated cheese on top and melt cheese.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients; shape into loaf in center of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until well browned.
Allow meat loaf to stand 10 minutes for easier slicing.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oven fried snapper
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Rinse fish and pat dry with paper towels.
Combine oil, garlic and dill in an oblong glass or Pyrex baking dish.
Place fish in mixture and turn, coating the fillets well.
Marinate for 2 to 3 hours, turning often.
Remove fish from marinade.
Roll fish in cheese, then in bread crumbs.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Baste often with marinade so fish does not burn.
When done, the fish will flake easily with a fork.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saut onions in skillet.
Add broccoli; heat until broccoli is thawed, stirring frequently.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: key lime pie
directions: *Can add food coloring to mixture, if you desire)

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain. Mix all other ingredients together; mix noodles too. Put in casserole dish and top with Ritz crackers, crushed, on top. Add butter on top of crackers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: layered salad
directions: Put bacon bits on top just before serving.
Let set for 24 hours.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Combine
tomato sauce, carrot, water, basil, and oregano in a 2 cup measure, cover, and microwave on high power for 2 minutes. Set aside.
Remove center vein from cabbage by using a pairing knife to cut along both sides of the vein, keeping the leaf in one piece.
Cook cabbage, covered, on high for 3 to 5 minutes or until limp.
Combine egg, crumbs, celery, onion, garlic powder, and pepper.
Add turkey.
Mix well and divide the mixture into 8 equal portions.
Place 1 portion on each cabbage leaf, fold in sides and roll up.
Place in a single layer in a casserole dish, cover, and cook on high for about 11 minutes or until done, turning a half turn once while cooking.
Drain excess liquid and top with the sauce.
Cook for 6 minutes more or until the sauce is heated through.

title: chicken stew casserole
directions: Stew chicken and debone.
Line pan with chicken; mix soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine in broth.
Mix Stove Top stuffing into broth.
Pour this on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: olive loaf
directions: Knead bread dough and roll into a rectangle (12 x 8-inch). Spread olives and cheese in the center.
Roll up and pinch the seams.
Place in baking dish and bake according to the package directions.
Serve warm.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil the potatoes and mash them.
Mix them with remaining ingredients.
Put in baked pie crust.
Put in oven at 250° for about 1 hour.
You can freeze the filling for later use.

title: panic
directions: Pour pie filling into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix (dry) over filling.
Pour melted margarine over top and sprinkle on nuts.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve warm plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar and evaporated milk in 2-quart saucepan on medium-high heat.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Stir in marshmallow cream.
Mix well.
Pour onto buttered plate.
Cool completely.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Lightly flour chicken breasts and saute in butter until golden.
Remove from pan and place on baking dish.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Add the soup and heat thoroughly.
Top chicken with ham and cheese, then pour the mushroom mixture over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together 1 cup sugar, cocoa and flour.
Add 2 egg yolks and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add vanilla and butter.
Beat egg whites; add 1/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons ice water.
Pour chocolate mixture in pie shell; top with meringue and brown.

title: tangy orange rice
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add celery and onion.
Cook until tender but not browned.
Add rice, salt, sugar, water and orange juice.
Cook until tender by bringing to a boil, then reducing heat.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes.
Stir and add orange rind.
Serve with ham, duck or chicken.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat milk until warm.
Stir in rice, stirring occasionally until it boils.
Lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes until rice is done.
Combine egg, sugar and vanilla.
Stir some of the rice mixture into egg mixture.
Put all in saucepan and cook for 3 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together dissolved baking soda, oil, and eggs. Sift together the dry ingredients and add to the above; beat. Add pumpkin and beat again. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: garlicky mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into chunks.
Cook potatoes until tender with peeled chopped garlic and salt, remove water and add cream cheese, butter, chopped chives and salt to taste.
Beat with mixer or mash with masher.
Serve hot with slice of butter and sprinkled with more chopped chives.

title: pork chops and gravy
directions: Brown pork chops in large skillet.
Drain off grease.
Mix soup, water and Kitchen Bouquet in bowl.
Add to pork chops. Cover and simmer until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water.
Add cranberry sauce (all juice), crushed pineapple, banana and nuts.
Pour 1/2 into baking dish and let set partly.
Add 1/2 sour cream on top and spread.
Add rest of jello mix and rest of sour cream.

title: angel food pie
directions: Sift sugar and cornstarch 3 times.
To this mixture, add boiling water and boil until thick (5 minutes).
Pour over beaten egg whites and beat well.
Add pineapple and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell and top with whipped cream.

title: lime fluff
directions: Mix Jell-O, cream cheese and pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: mexican stuffed pasta shells
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions, rinse and set aside.
In a bowl, combine picante sauce, water and tomato sauce. Put 1/2 tomato sauce mixture, chilies, black olives, 1/2 of all three cheese and 1/2 of the onion rings into the ground beef; mix well.
Pour 1/2 of the remaining tomato sauce mixture into the bottom of an 8 x 12-inch (or larger) casserole dish.
Stuff the pasta shells with beef mixture and place in the casserole dish. Pour the remaining tomato sauce over the stuffed shells.
Bake covered at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheeses and onion rings over the top and bake, uncovered, for 5 more minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peach dreams
directions: Puree peaches.
Add banana, yogurt, honey and ice.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add stuffing mix, soup, and sour cream.
Place in a greased casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: dill salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Cover and shake well. Chill.
Mix with macaroni salad.
Makes approximately 1 cup.

title: wild rice and mushrooms
directions: Cook and stir wild rice, mushrooms and onions in butter in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, about 5 minutes.
Stir in water, wine, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until rice is tender, 40 minutes. Stir in cheese.

title: butter rice
directions: Mix ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: egg salad sandwiches
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together the eggs, cheese, relish, sweet pepper, mayonnaise, dressing and mustard. If desired, use large cookie cutters to cut bread slices into shapes. Line 5 bread slices with lettuce. Spread on the egg mixture. Top with the remaining bread slices. If desired, garnish sandwiches with cherry tomatoes and/or carrots, using wooden toothpicks to secure.

title: crayfish gumbo
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients in cooking oil until tender. Add the tomato paste, water, oregano to taste, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and red pepper.
Cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Add 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup.
Add the raw crayfish.
Simmer another 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: pots de creme
directions: Put all ingredients into blender; cover and process at blend until smooth.
Pour into 6 cups or small containers.
Fill 2/3 full.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours or until of pudding like consistency.

title: fast and fancy peas
directions: Simmer all together about 8 to 10 minutes or until peas are soft.

title: turkey meatballs
directions: Mix first four ingredients and add 1/4 cup gravy.
Make into balls. In a 3-quart casserole, combine remainder of gravy, apple jelly and chili sauce.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes. Add meatballs.
Cover and microwave for 8 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: okra pickles
directions: Pack jar with okra.
Put in salt and garlic.
Boil vinegar and water.
Pour over okra and seal.
Put jar aside until sealed. Makes one quart.

title: cheese ball
directions: Beat the
cheeses
together.
Add
rest of ingredients. Shape into a ball and roll in crushed nuts.

title: deer tenderloin
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add meat and allow meat to absorb butter on both sides.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour water and bouillon cubes in pan and allow to cook until water is boiled out and brown.
Takes about 30 to 45 minutes to cook.

title: rocky road fudge candy
directions: Melt chocolate candy over double boiler.
Remove from heat and pour over nuts and marshmallows.
Stir and pour into a buttered 8-inch pan and chill.
Cut into squares before too cold.

title: punch
directions: Boil 10 cups of water with sugar until dissolved.
Add Kool-Aid, orange juice, pineapple juice, 4-quarts water, lemonade and ginger ale.
Serves 70 people.

title: lithuanian pressed cheese
directions: Mix together.
Pour into triangular cloth bag.
Press fat between 2 boards under weight (3 bricks or something heavy) for 2 days.
Remove from bag.
Refrigerate!

title: cauliflower and broccoli bake
directions: Steam the broccoli and cauliflower together; drain.
In a separate bowl, combine sour cream, soup, salt and pepper.
Pour over veggies and mix well.
Top with shelled and deveined shrimp. Bake at 375° for about 1/2 hour.

title: kahlua hot spiced apple cider
directions: Pour Kahlua into hot cider or apple juice.
Stir with cinnamon stick.

title: meatless mincemeat
directions: Chop tomatoes.
Cover with cold water and boil 5 minutes. Drain well.
Add other ingredients.
Return to fire and cook 30 to 40 minutes.
At last, cook slowly and stir (it might stick).
Can in pint jars and seal.
Makes good fried pies.
Serves 6.

title: best baked beans
directions: Thank God for dirty dishes.
They have a tale to tell.
While others are going hungry, we're eating very well.
With home and health and happiness, I shouldn't want to fuss.
For by this stack of evidence, God's very good to us.

title: strawberry pretzel jello salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzel sticks, sugar and melted margarine. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Beat these ingredients and spread on crust.
Dissolve strawberry jello with boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple to jello.
Chill these ingredients until slightly jelled, then pour over cream cheese mixture.
Chill 4 hours.

title: pacific rum salad
directions: Chop lettuce and green onions; add chicken and browned rice sticks.
Brown the rice sticks by frying in small amount of oil in pan.
They will swell and pop when put in the pan.
Mix remaining ingredients for dressing.
Toss with lettuce mix just before serving.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and chocolate.
Cover until boiling point is reached.
Boil until soft ball stage.
Add flavoring and cool without stirring to room temperature.
Beat until mixture is creamy, thick and will hold its shape when dropped from a teaspoon.
Then pour into well-buttered pan.

title: chicken salad ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, lemon juice, mayonnaise, salt, ground ginger and pepper
together
with
electric
mixer.
Stir
in chicken, eggs and onion.
Mix well and chill.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add sugar, oil, squash and vanilla. Cream together.

title: great apple pie
directions: Fill pastry-lined pie pan with apple slices.
Blend dry ingredients and sprinkle in between and over apples.
Dot with butter.
Put pan on baking sheet and bake at 400° in preheated oven for about 1 hour.

title: zippy potato soup
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon and onion.
Drain and set aside.
In a soup kettle or Dutch oven, cook the potatoes and carrot in water for 20 minutes or until tender (do not drain). Stir in the remaining ingredients and bacon mixture.
Cook for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield:
14 servings.

title: marinated fruit salad for 80
directions: Pare, core and slice apples, pears and peaches. Cut pineapple into chunks. Place fruit in a bowl and sprinkle with confectioners sugar to taste. Sprinkle with rum and cover bowl. Chill at least 6 hours so the sugar draws out fruit juices.

title: cheese chowder
directions: Bring water to a boil; add chopped vegetables.
Cover and cook until tender.
Do not drain.
In separate saucepan, melt margarine over low heat; add flour and stir into a smooth paste.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook and stir until thick.
Add cheese and cooked vegetables.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve hot. Serves 6.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Place water, cocoa and margarine in pan and bring to boil.
Remove from heat; pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch or 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate (1 or 2).
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 1 minute in blender on high or 2 minutes with hand beater.
Pour into plates. Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Check with knife inserted in center; must come out clean.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; place layer of whole graham crackers in dish.
Spread half of the pudding mixture over crackers; top with another layer of graham crackers and spread the remaining half of pudding mix, topping with third layer of graham crackers.
Pour cooled chocolate topping (recipe follows) over cake.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: easy bar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a greased rectangular pan.
Bake at 350° until brown and firm.
Cut when cool; don't overbake!

title: tamale pie
directions: Combine cornmeal, milk and egg in 2-quart glass casserole. Mix beef, powders and salt in 1-quart bowl.
Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until pinkness disappears.
Drain well and crumble meat.
Stir into cornmeal along with tomatoes, corn and olives.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes longer.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed.
Return drained noodles to kettle; stir in tuna, sour cream, milk, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Crumble 1/2 of cookies in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk together.
Mix sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese together. Stir with pudding and pour over cookies.
Crumble remaining cookies and sprinkle over top.
Chill.

title: rum pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and Crisco together. Add the remaining ingredients one at a time. Pour into greased and lined tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Put milk in a bowl.
Add eggs, mustard and salt and beat slightly.
Add vinegar and beat well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: spiced carrot strips
directions: Put carrots in saucepan.
Cover with water.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Combine next 4 ingredients; pour over carrots and toss to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: strawberry pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add crushed strawberries and crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Pour half of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream and cream cheese, which has been whipped together, over firm Jell-O.
Pour rest of Jell-O mixture over that.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: mexican chocolate rice cream
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and cornstarch in a pan.
Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat to the boiling point.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in rice and vanilla.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serve warm or chilled, as desired.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut broccoli; crumble bacon over top.
Add Miracle Whip, onions, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir all together.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: b and b relish
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and add 1 cup of salt.
Let stand approximately 4 hours.
Drain completely.
Bring to a boil the vinegar and sugar and add to tomato mixture.
Cook until it barely starts changing color.
Do not overcook.
Bottle in hot, sterile bottles.
This mixture must be very hot in order to seal.

title: hamburg ivan
directions: Fry onion and pepper in butter, add beef, mushrooms, salt, pepper and tarragon.
Fry 10 minutes stirring occasionally until meat is done.
Stir in sour cream, heat through and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over noodles.

title: black bean soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine first 3 ingredients.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Cut beef sausage lengthwise in half, then crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Add sausage and soup to vegetables; stir to blend.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve with yogurt and parsley on top, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dried beef sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in refrigerator.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and stir over medium heat until mixture boils and bubbles to top; stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chocolate morsels.
Stir until melted; add pecans.
Drop with teaspoon on waxed paper.
Chill until set.
Makes 24.

title: jane burr's dump bars
directions: Dump all ingredients except chocolate chips in a bowl.
Mix with a spoon until moistened.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top; do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool and cut into bars.

title: broccoli lasagna
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving, in 2-quart saucepan over medium-low heat, heat undiluted broccoli soup and frozen broccoli until broccoli is thawed.

In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon hot salad oil, cook carrots and onion until lightly browned. Reduce heat to low. Stir in 1/4 cup water. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are very tender; remove to bowl.
In the same skillet over high heat, in 3 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook mushrooms until lightly browned and all liquid has evaporated; stir in carrot mixture.
While vegetables are cooking, prepare noodles as label directs.
Drain.
In a bowl, mix Mozzarella, Ricotta and eggs.

title: tabasco hamburgers
directions: Combine ground round, onion and green peppers with 3/4 cup barbecue sauce.
Shape into 12 hamburgers.
Barbecue, basting frequently with the remaining barbecue sauce.
Serve with barbecue sauce and your favorite toppings.

title: sally's cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in salted water; add butter and cheese.
Stir until well melted.
Add worcestershire sauce and 1 tsp. paprika. Beat eggs and stir milk into them.
Stir into grits.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with water, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Crumble butter, sugar and flour. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. Nuts may be added before crust if desired.

title: penuche nut frosting
directions: Put brown sugar, milk and Crisco in saucepan; set over low heat until dissolved.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Let boil 1 minute; beat until thick enough to spread.

title: baked italian bread
directions: Slice bread diagonally in both directions. Stuff sliced cheese into openings. Place bread on large piece of foil on top of cookie sheet. Mix butter with seasonings and mushrooms. Pour butter mix over bread. Seal foil over bread. Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add the remaining ingredients; blend.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting; sprinkle with nutmeg and sugar mixed together.

title: chicken coronet
directions: Boil chicken for 35 minutes.
Cool and debone.
Place thawed broccoli in bottom of greased flat baking dish.
Add chicken pieces.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon together; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Serve over wild rice.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine onion mixture, hash brown potatoes, sour cream, celery soup and Cheddar cheese in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Spoon potato mixture into a lightly greased 11 x 17 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed cereal and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute the oleo, onion and bell pepper until just tender. Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Meanwhile, grate some sharp Cheddar cheese; sprinkle over top and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: fruit cocktail-jello salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, stir in jello to dissolve.
Add Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: meal-in-one casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of 4 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish with a layer of frozen potato puffs.
Drain green beans; place on top of potato puffs.
Top green beans with ham; end with another layer of potato puffs.
Combine celery soup, mayonnaise and mustard; pour over ham, potatoes and beans. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: cranberry cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add milk, orange juice, rind and egg.
Blend in all dry ingredients plus nuts and cranberries. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet and bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: the prairie schooner(punch)
directions: Heat water and sugar to boiling (sugar dissolves).
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Put some of punch in gelatin ring to freeze.
Chill punch.
Freeze ring.
Float ring in punch when serving.
Yields 60 (1/2 cup size) servings.

title: brownies for the crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients. Stir in pecans. Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° until done.

title: jelly corn muffins
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk gradually.
Add beaten egg and melted shortening.
Fill greased muffin pans 1/4 full.
Put a teaspoon of jelly on top of the batter.
Cover with more batter and bake at 400° to 425° for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp with garlic and oyster sauce
directions: Make a marinade by combining the egg white, cornstarch, sesame oil and salt.
Marinate the shrimp in the mixture for up to 2 hours.
When ready to prepare, heat the vegetable oil in a skillet over high heat and add the shrimp.
Stir until shrimp are barely pink.
Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside.
Remove half the oil from the skillet; add the garlic and stir for a few seconds over high heat.
Add the oyster sauce.
Return the shrimp to the skillet and cook until done.
Do not overcook.
Garnish with the scallion.
Serves 4.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pears, pineapple and peaches.
Mix instant pudding with peach juice.
Pour over fruit.
Let set overnight.
Add bananas and serve.

title: pot roast with mushroom gravy
directions: Put roast in roasting pan with lid.
Mix soups, water and mushrooms until blended.
Pour over roast.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 5 hours.
Add more water while cooking if it thickens too much.
When meat is tender, cut into large pieces.
Put gravy over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: spaghetti pie casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in butter, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and egg.
Spread evenly in pan. Saute ground beef, onion and green pepper in oil until brown. Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, oregano, sugar and garlic salt. Spread cottage cheese over top.

title: fresh strawberry soup
directions: Combine berries, juice, water and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water; stir.
Add cardamom and stir into soup.
Cook until thickened.
Allow soup to cool, and serve chilled.
Good and different.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain, rinse and set aside.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Boil potato until soft; mash.
Add vanilla, salt and sugar. Mixture will be consistency of dough.
Roll out onto oiled paper. Roll out with more powdered sugar to about the thickness of a pie crust.
Spread with peanut butter; roll up like a jelly roll.
Put in refrigerator for an hour; slice thin.

title: squash and pepper casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and brown sugar in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until rice is done.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain well.
Add chili powder, soup and sauce.
Let simmer 45 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients. Let boil, then cook about 1 hour.

title: hamburger corn-pone pie
directions: Brown meat and onion in melted shortening.
Add seasoning and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add kidney beans.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Top with corn bread batter and bake in a hot oven at 425° for 20 minutes. Serves 4.
Serve with cabbage and carrot slaw, orange and banana cup and brownies.

title: red barn dressing
directions: Mix together with wire whisk.
Do not use blender; it will separate.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Toss all vegetables.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix mayonnaise into vegetables.
Serve immediately. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: freezer cookies
directions: Mix all together and shape into logs; freeze.
When ready to bake, slice thin.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
You may keep them in the freezer indefinitely.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo until slightly brown.
Add meat and brown.
Add salt, pepper and uncooked rice.
Chop cabbage into a 2-quart baking dish.
Spoon meat mixture over cabbage.
Mix soup and water; pour over cabbage and meat.
Cover with foil. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with cheese and heat until cheese melts.

title: salmon cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill. Roll into ball. I roll into 2 logs. Roll in crushed pecans and dried parsley.

title: southern living cajun chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with garlic powder; set aside.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger
together; drain grease.
Place in bottom of baking dish.
Pour sauce over.
Next, place cheese on this.
Mix together biscuit mix, milk and eggs.
Pour over top of all.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: boneless chicken breast
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix egg and milk; dip chicken and roll in crackers.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn chicken over.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: *May use frozen vegetables, cauliflower, carrots, potatoes, broccoli.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: In a large bowl combine bread, chips and cinnamon.

title: mildy's pineapple pudding
directions: Cook sugar, eggs and pineapple until thick. Layer crackers and filling and top with whipped cream or Cool Whip or your favorite whipped cream.

title: sauce piquant
directions: Get up before work.
Marinate roast in Wish-Bone for 24 hours. Next morning before you put your work clothes on, remove roast from pan.
Sling stuff off roast.
Season well on both sides.
Roll in flour.
Quickly fry and brown on both sides.
Don't eat yet!
Place in crock-pot on high.
Add crushed garlic, grated onion, soup and water.
Let cook until you get home from work.
Turn to low.
Add tomato sauce.
Taste several times while adding cayenne pepper. Stop when your mouth burns!
(This will depend on how much French is in your blood.)
Continue to cook on low, adding everything you missed when seasoning.
Cook a pot of rice.
When rice is done, bless the food and get after it!

title: cheesy olive appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In a small bowl, blend cheese and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in a saucepan on low heat. When melted, add the other ingredients; mix well. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: summer chicken salad
directions: In a bowl, combine the chicken, celery, grapes and raisins. Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Mix well. Stir in pecans. Serve on lettuce. Garnish with tomatoes, if desired. Yields 2 to 3 servings.

title: fettuccine with sun-dried tomato cream
directions: Cover tomatoes with boiling water; let stand 10 minutes. Drain.
Place tomatoes and garlic in food processor; process until coarsely chopped.
Add cream cheese and oregano and process until well blended.
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in cream cheese mixture and sour cream.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Toss fettuccine with oil.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serve immediately.

title: english muffin and crabmeat
directions: Cut muffins in half.
Drain crabmeat and add Old English cheese, oleo, mayonnaise and garlic powder.
Mix well and spread on muffins.
Cut each into 8 pieces.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, broil until cheese melts.

title: jade ring salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in 2 cups hot water.
Pour 3/4 cup into mold and chill.
Whip remainder.
Blend in either the vegetables or fruit, cottage cheese and mayonnaise.
Let set on firm layer.

title: megan's butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; stir in salt, vanilla and flour.
Dough will be stiff.
Roll like icebox cookies.
Chill.
Slice.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Mix orange Jell-O, water, 3 eggs, oil and orange flavoring. Beat 3 minutes with spoon or wire whip (no electric mixer) until batter is mixed well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake is done.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix above for 5 minutes (excluding wafers).
Place wafers in bottom of cupcake liners.
Fill with about a tablespoon of mixture.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 30.

title: sausage brunch
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Spray pan with Pam.
Spread croutons on bottom of pan.
Add cooked sausage; top with cheese. Half cup cheese can be reserved to add over topping.
Beat eggs in milk and dry mustard; pour over cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion into milk.
Blend in flour, egg and salt.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls into hot fat.
Brown both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 3 dozen.
Serve with applesauce.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Blend first five ingredients. Let stand overnight.
Add large Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In a small bowl mix sugar, salt and baking powder.
In a large bowl beat eggs; add milk, then other dry mixture and beat until well mixed.
If mixture is too thick, add a little more milk. Fill electric skillet 1/2 to 3/4 full with oil.
Heat oil to 380° to 400° (very hot).

title: italian steak
directions: Place steaks in shallow dish. Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over steaks.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 4 to 6 hours, turning occasionally.

title: dad's favorite white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and vanilla.
(Add about 3 tablespoons flour to chopped nuts and fruit, mix lightly.)
Fold in mixture.
Grease tube pan.
Cut wax paper to fit bottom of pan.
Pour in mixture.
You may add nuts and cherries on top.
Bake at 230° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours gradually turn temperature up to 300°.

title: beef hash
directions: Grind up beef, (you could accumulate small amounts of leftover beef until you have enough to equal 2 cups, ground up.
Place the leftovers in a Baggie and freeze until needed), onions and potatoes.
Place in frying pan with butter and seasonings; mix well.
Fry over medium heat for 20 minutes, turning occasionally. Can also be baked 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Serve with hot fudge sauce or Hershey's chocolate syrup (optional).

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine melted butter, onion, salt, cheese, broccoli and beaten eggs.
Blend together.
Stir in muffin mix.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cut into serving size squares.

title: scallop soup
directions: Place wine, water, peppercorns, bay leaf, parsley, shallots and chicken broth in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and add scallops (cut into bite-size).
Boil them gently in this liquid for approximately 10 minutes, or until they are tender. Strain the broth into a bowl.
Save the scallops and shallots but discard parsley, peppercorns and bay leaf.
Melt butter in a small saucepan and stir in flour with a whisk.
Add light cream and cheese.
As soon as this mixture thickens, remove from heat and stir in the scallop broth.
Place egg yolk, scallops, shallots and 2 cups of the
liquid in a blender or run through a food mill. Puree well.
Return all ingredients to a large soup pan and heat. Do not boil.
Serve in small portions garnished with minced parsley.
Serves 4.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Put 6 slices bread, buttered side down, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover bread with cheese.
Sprinkle ham over.
Layer other 6 slices bread over cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together and pour over casserole.
Melt and drizzle 1/3 cup butter over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting and serving.

title: fluffy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Leave in pan.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Place 1/2 of mix into one pie crust and the other 1/2 mix in other pie crust. Carefully place the top of each pie crust on each pie pressing the sides together. Place oven on 375 degrees and cook for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust is brown. Serves 12.

title: french market soup mix
directions: Mix all of above together and divide into 13 even 2 cup packages.

title: asparagus bake
directions: Melt butter or margarine in small saucepan.
Stir in salt and flour.
Cook until boiling.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils 1 minute.
Add pimento.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook onion, celery, carrots and margarine until transparent. Add flour and cook slighlty.
Add water, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper and nutmeg; stir until thickened.
Add broccoli; cook 5 to 10 minutes, then run all through blender.
Cream - thin soup to desired consistency.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 (8-inch) pans.
